title: May 13 NYS Safe Streets Coalition Lobby Day
description:
Join the New York Safe Streets Coalition May 13th Lobby Day! Families for Safe Streets, Transportation Alternatives, and other organizations from across New York City and New York State will be taking on Albany together and showing that we are a powerful force to contend with. But we need YOU to join us. This is our chance to talk directly with state legislators, tell them our stories, and make a real impact for safe streets. 

We have the tools to cure the traffic violence crisis, but we need bold action from our lawmakers, and we need you to deliver that message.

We will meet with elected officials to discuss the SAFE Streets package.
Learn more about the package at nyssafestreets.org.

RSVP now to secure your spot for what‚Äôs sure to be an inspiring day of action!

Transportation to Albany from NYC and Kingston is provided by bus. Train tickets may be provided as needed, for people with special needs. 
We will be doing trainings to prepare you for the lobby day on Friday, May 9th at 12pm and Monday, May 12th at 5:30pm.

title: Every Tuesday #DemocracyRushHour: 8am at University/Farley
description:
Every Tuesday, citizens have been reaching commuters on University Ave in Madison, WI with pro-democracy messages and a targeted theme each week. During morning rush hour hundreds of commuters have to sit at this red light and look at our signs! This is an opportunity to pierce through our current news (and disinformation) ecosystems with concise pro-democracy ideas, messages, and calls to action.

In your confirmation email, you will receive a link to a google doc and my email so you can get the weekly topic. If you don't know the topic of the week or don't want to make new signs, you can always just make one telling drivers to call their senators and rep! We will also have cardboard/markers available if you need it.

This is a non-violent and non-confrontational event. We have a lot of fun and feel free to join us for any amount of time!

title: Rush-hour Resistance Rally @ Melrose curve in Phoenix
description:
Big events with thousands of people are great. But we also need local, more frequent rallies that show locals that they're not alone in this fight. 

So I made one! 

Every Wednesday, @ 7am, we'll gather at Copper Star Coffee in midtown Phoenix to grab a beverage, walk down to the rainbow crosswalk across 7th Avenue, and show the busy morning commuters that they are not alone.

Peak traffic time seems to be from 7:30 to 8:30a. Yes, it's already hot in Phoenix, so plan accordingly. Bill from Copper Star has graciously (and excitedly!) offered to let us use the shop as a cooling off and bio-break place as needed.

Spread the word. Come join us. Or start your own!

All the details you need are at [RhRR.us](https://rhrr.us).

Love this idea and want to start your own Rush-hour Resistance Rally in your area? Groovy! Let's make that happen!

title: Four Corners in Lenexa  Standing Rally
description: As citizens, we can‚Äôt let the policies and actions of the Federal Government and unelected billionaires be normalized, but we can only stop what‚Äôs going on by coming together.  A STANDING RALLY  will draw attention to the situation, encouraging our neighbors to join with us. We will rally every Saturday morning from 11 AM ‚Äì 12 PM.  Stay for the full hour or come by when and for how long you can. We will peacefully line the sidewalk on all four corners of 87th Parkway and Maurer Road,  holding signs on issues that are most meaningful to us or just simply standing in support of our neighbors and our country.  If sitting is more comfortable for you, you are very welcome to bring mobility or lawn chairs!! There is room for everyone!
accessibility_notes:
Here are a couple of notes on logistics.
Please be especially mindful of parking.  For example, if you live relatively nearby, please consider walking.  If you drive, there is street parking on the residential streets to the north and also a bit further on the south.  About ¬Ω mile down on the west, there is a large civic campus garage at 17201 W 87th St. Pkwy.  In addition, on the SE, SW, and NW sides of the intersection, there are restaurants and shops with big, but commercially owned parking lots meant for customers.  (Please note that if you become a customer, it‚Äôs fine to bring snacks to the rally that you have bought, but please take any empty snack containers back home with you, when you leave. In any case, no matter which direction you are coming from, if it is possible, please try to park before you reach the intersection to save on congestion and choose a spot as far away as you feel comfortable walking from, leaving closer spots to those who can‚Äôt walk as far.
The rally will start on the SE corner, but as more folks arrive, we will disperse to the SW, NW, and NE corners, as well.   If you cross from one side to another, please pay particular attention to cars turning right as you cross! 
 Participants should bring their own signs (if they want to hold them).  Note that sticks supporting the signs can‚Äôt be pointed at either end.  Also, in designing content for the signs, please remember that children will be present.  
Please stand only along the sidewalks parallel to the street and not on the grass.  However, also be sure to allow pedestrian access to the sidewalk and businesses.   We are not expecting issues, but keep in mind that a core principle behind our events is a commitment to nonviolent action.  Remember to de-escalate any potential confrontation with someone,  who disagrees with you. And of course, follow directions from our excellent Lenexa police, if asked.
We will not have speakers. The plan will simply be to hold the signs we have made and wave, if that feels right.  We expect that a lot of passing cars will honk back in approval! 
Finally, please note that all our organizers will be wearing lanyards with badges reading  ‚ÄúStanding Rally Corner Captain or ‚ÄúStanding Rally Media/City Liaison‚Äù.  If you see other folks with ‚ÄúPress‚Äù marked on their clothing or who are giving direction to you, know that they are not part of Four Corners and are not endorsed or vetted by us.
See you soon.  Let‚Äôs show our neighbors ‚Äúwhat Democracy Looks Like‚Äù!!
P.S.  If you want to post an inspiring (!) story about your experience, please add #FourCornersinLenexa to your post!

title: Hands Across Chicagoland
description:
Join tens of thousands of your fellow Chicago-area citizens as we form a human chain of conscience across Chicagoland in peaceful protest against Trump‚Äôs illegal and authoritarian actions and the GOP's failure to defend the Constitution. 

Bring signs, wear black, and make some noise.

We will line sidewalks along 30 miles from Aurora to Chicago along Ogden Ave, 26th Street and California Ave to Douglass Park. This is a peaceful protest. We will not block streets or businesses along the route.

Please go to www.handsacrosschi.com and enter your zip code to get an assigned location along the route. This is important so that we can spread people out evenly along the route, while keeping people closer to where they live. ***Ignore the map below; that is not your assigned location***

President Trump has defied court orders and forcibly sent people to a torture dungeon in El Salvador without a hearing or due process. Now he claims he‚Äôs unable to bring them back. He's ignored court rulings and arrested judges. If he can do this to them, he can do it to anyone.

These are the actions of a dictator‚Äînot a democratically elected president. Silence is not an option. When leaders cross the line into authoritarianism, it‚Äôs up to us‚Äîthe people‚Äîto push back. This protest is about more than politics. It's about defending basic human dignity, civil liberties, and the idea that no one is above the law.

Bring your family, friends, neighbors, coworkers‚Äîanyone who believes in freedom and democracy.

***Confirmed Sponsors*** (if you'd like your group to be involved, email info@dupagedemocrats.com):
Batavia Township Democrats, Citizen Action/Illinois, Democratic Party of DuPage County, Democratic Women of DuPage County (DWDC), Illinois Democratic Women, Illinois Federation of Teachers, Illinois State Association of Letter Carriers, IL Veterans for Change, In Unison (Joliet), Indivisible Batavia Aurora Area, Indivisible DuPage, Indivisible Evanston, Indivisible Illinois, Indivisible Naperville, Indivisible Skokie Morton Grove Lincolnwood, Indivisible Westside, Indivisible West Suburban Chicago, Lisle Township Democratic Organization, Milton Township Democratic Organization, Naperville Township Democratic Organization, Operation Swing State, Personal PAC, Progressives for Change (Elmhurst), The People‚Äôs Lobby, West Suburban Teachers Union Local 571, We Can Lead Change (Fox Valley), Winfield Township Democratic Organization, York Township Democratic Organization

title: 5/14 Stop Elon Musk Rally!
description:
### Join Indivisible Greater Vancouver (IGV) and MoveOn Clark County for a peaceful protest at Vancouver's Tesla dealership! 

Unvetted DOGE operatives hired by Musk are accessing our data, impounding funds allocated by Congress, and crippling federal agencies. This empowers the surveillance state and paves the way for billionaire tax cuts, deregulation and more. 

We'll march on the sidewalk/right of way outside Vancouver's Tesla showroom on Fourth Plain Blvd., staying on public property. Park on the street or in the surrounding neighborhood, not in business parking lots. Bring a large sign to let everyone know we stand united against Musk, DOGE, and unelected oligarchs!

We at IGV strongly believe that peaceful, non-violent activism offers social movements the most power to effect change. Through peaceful protests, we set an example of making our voices heard with dignity, empowered by truth. IGV does not condone intimidation, threats, vandalism, interference with access to a business, or any other lawless actions. If instigators or our opponents attempt to violate our commitment to non-violence, we will try to de-escalate them and will end the event if needed to maintain a safe environment.

We know many of us have very strong feelings about issues and people at this time. If you feel that you may have difficulty remaining nonviolent, please do not attend this activity.

### Join Indivisible Greater Vancouver (IGV) and MoveOn Clark County for a peaceful protest at Vancouver's Tesla dealership! 

### NEW SATURDAY TIMES: 4 pm - 6 pm

Unvetted DOGE operatives hired by Musk are accessing our data, impounding funds allocated by Congress, and crippling federal agencies. This empowers the surveillance state and paves the way for billionaire tax cuts, deregulation and more. 

We'll march on the sidewalk/right of way outside Vancouver's Tesla showroom on Fourth Plain Blvd., staying on public property. Park on the street or in the surrounding neighborhood, not in business parking lots. Bring a large sign to let everyone know we stand united against Musk, DOGE, and unelected oligarchs!

We at IGV strongly believe that peaceful, non-violent activism offers social movements the most power to effect change. Through peaceful protests, we set an example of making our voices heard with dignity, empowered by truth. IGV does not condone intimidation, threats, vandalism, interference with access to a business, or any other lawless actions. If instigators or our opponents attempt to violate our commitment to non-violence, we will try to de-escalate them and will end the event if needed to maintain a safe environment.

We know many of us have very strong feelings about issues and people at this time. If you feel that you may have difficulty remaining nonviolent, please do not attend this activity.

title: PDX Car Caravan Protest 2.0
description:
For May 11 protest:

Meet in the public lot behind the Flanders Professional Building. It‚Äôs in the middle of the block bordered by NW 22nd and 23rd, and NW Everett and Flanders.

Please back into a spot by 1:45 so you‚Äôre positioned to pull into the caravan when we leave at 2:00. 

The 5/11 route will have some slow stretches with quite quite a few pauses at lights and intersections. We use these pauses as part of the protest: shout, chant, show your signs, pass out pamphlets or buttons, etc. We do get split up, but we all get back together at the end of these stretches. We‚Äôll talk about traffic and safety and a few tips to keep it all together at 1:45.
The 5/11 PDX Car Caravan Protest will end at the ICE building in S Portland. A Mother‚Äôs Day Vigil and Memorial will be held there at 4:00, which is close to our ETA. You are invited to join this additional protest put on by PDX Contra las Deportaciones to protest and remember the victims of the Trump administration‚Äôs cruel abductions and deportations.



This a local Indivisible event!

PDX Car Caravan Protest 1.0 was active weekly or more for over a year, 2020-21, and protested racial injustice and police brutality. We are back in version 2.0 as a raucous motorized protest for people who love justice and hate injustice of all varieties. If you are outraged and need to protest but for whatever reason don‚Äôt (always)do crowds, standing and marching, roll with us. Keep your foot on the gas. 

More details on bluesky and Facebook: PDX Car Caravan Protest 2.0
accessibility_notes: You arrive and can remain in your own vehicle for the entire protest. We give a short traffic safety orientation and provide a written handout. If you need to remain in your vehicle during the orientation, just let us know so we can make sure you can access the information.

title: NO KINGS! TAKE BACK THE FLAG!
description:
FLAG DAY 2025!
MAGA has tried to use our flag to spread hate and division.
But that's not our flag!
Our flag represents hope, freedom and the sacrifices of generations of Americans.
It's time to take back the flag!! FLAG DAY 2025!
In America, we don‚Äôt put up with would-be kings. NO KINGS is a national day of action and mass mobilization in response to increasing authoritarian excesses and corruption from Trump and his allies. We‚Äôve watched as they‚Äôve cracked down on free speech, detained people for their political views, threatened to deport American citizens, and defied the courts. They‚Äôve done this all while continuing to serve and enrich their billionaire allies.

üö®On Saturday, June 14, we‚Äôre taking to the streets nationwide. We‚Äôre not gathering to feed his ego. We‚Äôre building a movement that leaves him behind.üö®

The flag doesn‚Äôt belong to Donald Trump. It belongs to us. We‚Äôre not watching history happen. We‚Äôre making it.

On June 14th, we‚Äôre showing up everywhere he isn‚Äôt‚Äîto say no thrones, no crowns, no kings.
accessibility_notes: There are elevators at all of the intersections.If you are not able or choose not to march, feel free to rally in front of NYNY.

title: TRUST Act Now - InterFaith Day of Action
description:
Our many religious, spiritual, and ethical traditions teach us that we have a moral imperative to welcome the stranger, provide for those in need, and protect the vulnerable in our communities. 

That‚Äôs where we‚Äôre inviting faith leaders and all people of conscience to join us at the CT State Capitol, for a Faith Day of Action at the Capitol Building to talk with legislators about why they MUST protect our immigrant communities and pass a strengthened TRUST Act.

The TRUST Act (HB 7212) is a bill that would protect our CT immigrant community from ICE abductions and protect CT local resources from being used to further mass deportations.

The Trust Act will send a strong message that Connecticut protects the safety and humanity of all its residents, regardless of immigration status. 

**Schedule for the the day:**

- Press conference: 10:30am-11:15am

- Training: 11:30am-12pm

- Talking with legislators 12pm - 2pm

*Never been to the Capitol before or spoken with legislators?* No worries! We‚Äôll provide you with all the materials you need and we‚Äôll have TRUST Act Now! Coalition leaders present to guide all attendees!

We‚Äôre calling for a full boycott of Avelo Airlines and organizing protests a weekly protest at our local airport. 

We will be on the sidewalk leading to the Charles M. Schulz Sonoma County Airport, which is for now a hub for Avelo's flights at a time when a maximum number of travelers will see our protest. It is also a good opportunity to protest federal layoffs with the FAA.

You can park nearby or take SMART to get there.

title: Accountability Tuesdays - Jeff Van Drew has got to go!
description:
**Accountability Tuesdays: Van Drew, Meet with Us**

WE ARE DEMANDING A TOWN HALL - The excuse is that his district is too big and so all we get is tele town halls - 

**Host:**  
Atlantic County Indivisible

**When:**  
**Tuesday, April 29 2025 ‚Äî 4:30 PM**  
(Repeats every other Tuesday)

**Where:**  
**Jeff Van Drew‚Äôs District Office** 

Northfield Office

1001 Tilton Road
Suite 101
Northfield, NJ 08225
Phone: (609) 625-5008

**Event Description:**  
Congressman Jeff Van Drew is supposed to represent **us**‚Äîbut he only meets with **donors**, **special interests**, and **MAGA extremists**.

He hasn‚Äôt held a public town hall in years, and his voting record speaks for itself:
- **Voted against certifying the 2020 election results**
- Opposed **abortion rights**, **student loan forgiveness**, and **LGBTQ+ protections**
- Supports efforts to **defund public education** and deny the climate crisis
- Turns his back on working people and silences dissent in our district

So we show up. Peacefully. Persistently. Every other Tuesday.

> **Donors get the meetings. Constituents get ignored.**

We‚Äôre rallying outside his **Northfield District Office** to demand visibility, accountability, and representation. This is a **peaceful protest** to let our neighbors‚Äîand our congressman‚Äîknow we are watching.

**What to Bring:**
- Signs (or use ours!)  
- Friends, neighbors, coworkers  
- Water, weather-appropriate clothing  
- Your voice and your presence  

**Accessibility:**  
- Public sidewalk with parking nearby  
- No marching‚Äîstand or sit as long as you‚Äôd like  
- Family-friendly and open to all

We‚Äôve coordinated with local police to ensure a safe, orderly, nonviolent demonstration. Everyone who believes in democracy is welcome.

title: Tesla Takedown Protest in Seaside, Ca
description:
Join us EVERY Saturday at 12pm to protest Elon Musk and his unconstitutional dismantling of the federal government. Bring a sign, your friends, musical instruments, whatever makes you happy.

*** Please be aware that we'e seen some counter protestors at these events. They're mostly loud and obnoxious, trying to provoke a response. The best thing to do is ignore them entirely and not give them the attention they crave. ***

We have more people every week! It's a good time and we get a lot of positive feedback from passing cars. It might seem like a small thing but every little bit helps. And it feels good to DO SOMETHING so come on down!

Elon Musk and DOGE are engaged in an administrative coup of the federal government. They have taken control of the federal payment system and are unilaterally suspending funds appropriated by congress, in clear violation of the Constitution.

They have already caused immense harm by dismantling USAID and have set their sights on everything from the Social Security to the NIH and the FAA next. Make no mistake, their end goal is the destruction of the US Federal Government and its ability to check corporate power and provide basic services.

How this develops in Washington remains to be seen, but as US citizens we can exercise our 1st Amendment right to peacefully protest. Elon Musk's liquid net worth is largely based on Tesla stock, which is currently valued at 10-15 times that of other car companies. Driving down the share price is a direct attack on Elon's power.

The stakes couldn‚Äôt be higher. No one is coming to save us‚Äînot politicians, not the media. It's up to the people to stand up and fight for democracy and against fascism.

title: Democracy Thursday Visibility Rally - Take a Stand for our Democracy

location.venue: Along Broadway near the corner of 6th St. SW (do not stand in front of the fire station)

description:
Join the DFL and local community for our standing Thursday afternoon rally for a strong democracy. These events are informal and will now always be 4:30 - 6:00 PM on Thursdays on Broadway, near the corner of 6th St SW. Although the DFL is promoting these rallies, these issues are primarily nonpartisan -- everyone who wants to protect our democracy is welcome to join us. Show up for part or all of the event, it doesn‚Äôt matter. Bring the issues that matter most to you, make your most bold and creative sign, and stand with your community in solidarity. 

We need every voice. Do not underestimate how much this matters. Almost all of the cars driving by honk in encouragement, and it lifts community spirits to see people standing bravely and speaking out. The more people out there, the louder the message. If you are new to protests, this is a great way to start. We will have a few extra signs for those of you who don‚Äôt have one. If you can‚Äôt rally with us, please drive by and make some noise in your car!!

'If everyone has just a little bit of courage, then no one has to be a hero" -Rep McBride

Let‚Äôs get after it, Rochester!

Sign-up/questions:  no registration is required, contact olmsted2024dfl@gmail.com with questions. 

(Please note that we also provide sign making support -supplies and design help- on Tuesday afternoons at the Rochester DFL offices from 4-6pm)

title: Be the Light in the Darkness

address_lines: Along Florida/Kirby all the way to Hessel Park

description:
Donald Trump & his cronies throughout the government are doing everything that they can to make their opposition feel isolated, alone, and powerless. But courage is contagious, and we can make our courage visible by standing as a literal light in the darkness.

title: No Veteran Left Behind | A Memorial Day Silent Protest
description:
This is a SILENT protest to bring visibility to and honor our Veterans hosted by Indivisible Acworth. We invite our community to stand in solidarity with our veterans.

We are hosting a silent protest on Sunday, May 25th at the Cobb VA North Clinic in Marietta to raise awareness regarding the assault to veterans' benefits, entitlements, and access to care. 

On Thursday, the US Department of Veterans Affairs ended a mortgage rescue program that has helped almost 20,000 veterans avoid foreclosure and keep their homes. Approximately 90,000 VA loans are at risk of foreclosure and this number continues to increase as more and more veterans are illegally terminated from their Federal jobs by DOGE. 

If the administration can cut this program, reduce vital staff, and create restrictions to the Suicide Hotline, what else do they plan to cut? 

We must gather in solidarity behind the veteran community and we must stand up and fight in memory of the veterans who stood up to, and lost their lives in their combat against fascism and human rights violations.

Because Memorial Day is a solemn day of remembrance, we ask that protestors do not scream and that signage remains RESPECTFUL and relates ONLY to cuts to veterans programs, supporting our veterans, supporting VA staff, and signs that honor the fallen and defend the living.

Sign ideas include, but are not limited to: ÔªøÔªøÔªøÔªø

Ôªø"Honor the Fallen. Care for the Living."ÔªøÔªø
"They Fought for Us ‚Äî Now We Fight for Them."
"Cuts to VA = Dishonor to Their Sacrifice."
"Memorial Day Is More Than Words ‚Äî Fund the VA!"
Ôªø"Project 2025: Betraying the Oath to Those Who Took One."
"Protect the VA, Protect the Promise."
"Fully Staff the VA ‚Äî Lives Depend on It."
"No More Delays. No More Cuts. No More Excuses."
"Veterans Before Politics."
"We Lost Brothers/Sisters in War ‚Äî Don‚Äôt Lose Them to Policy."
"No Vet Should Fight for Benefits They Earned in Combat."ÔªøÔªø
"From Battlefield to Bureaucracy ‚Äî Stop the War on Veterans."
"Veterans Deserve Dignity, Not Budget Cuts."

Again, please keep signs respectful. There is a time and place for more humorous or abrasive messaging, but we are showing solidarity with our vets.

Elon's busy wreaking havoc, and we're busy letting our fellow citizens and elected officials know how we feel about it.

Elon Musk is an unelected political actor. He's causing tremendous damage to our government, and is hurting people who work(ed) for governmental agencies, and people who are served by governmental agencies. Elon Musk is hurting our country and its people.

- to grow in numbers and courage and resilience

- to be kind, and have fun!

We may see a counter protester. If so, the best thing to do is just ignore them and spend our time and energy waving to motorists. Let's keep things 100% non-confrontational in words and body language.

title: Stand Up for Democracy March and Rally
description:
Join Democracy Action Network (DAN) for a powerful day of democratic engagement, community solidarity, and peaceful action. 

On Flag Day 2025, we stand together to reaffirm our commitment to democratic principles, constitutional governance, and human rights for all.

In a time when democratic institutions face unprecedented challenges, we invite concerned citizens of all backgrounds, beliefs, and political affiliations to unite in defense of our shared democratic values. This nonpartisan rally brings together speakers, community leaders, and grassroots activists to inspire action and build momentum for democratic renewal.

The Stand Up for Democracy Rally and March will feature:

- Keynote addresses from prominent civil rights advocates and democracy experts
- Community-led workshops on civic engagement and grassroots organizing
- Interactive educational displays about democratic principles and voting rights
- Family-friendly activities and entertainment
- A peaceful march from Palisades Park to Santa Monica City Hall

Democracy isn't just something we have‚Äîit's something we do. Join us as we stand up for the democratic principles that unite us as Americans: equality under the law, freedom of expression, fair elections, and government that answers to its people.

Transportation: The Downtown Santa Monica Metro E Line station provides direct rail access from Downtown LA and is a short walk from the rally site. Additional bus service and bike parking will be available.

Accessibility: The event is fully accessible, with accommodations for all participants.

For more information: Visit democracyactionnetwork.org/standup2025 or email info@democracyactionnetwork.org

The Democracy Action Network (DAN) is a nonpartisan grassroots organization founded in 2024 dedicated to defending democratic institutions, promoting civic engagement, and fostering inclusive democracy through nonviolent action and community empowerment.
#StandUpForDemocracy #DemocracyMatters #PeacefulAction

title: Victory Red Day
description:
A campaign for a¬†Day of Female Solidarity and Empowerment¬†on¬†June 24, 2025‚Äîthe anniversary of Roe v. Wade‚Äôs repeal. The idea is simple yet powerful: women and supporters of women everywhere wear red lipstick¬†as a symbol of strength, resilience, and the ongoing fight for gender equality.

Victory Red lipstick has long been a symbol of women‚Äôs power, particularly during World War II, when it was worn by women on the home front to represent strength, defiance, and patriotism. During this time, women stepped into roles previously held by men, contributing to the war effort while asserting their independence and resilience. They stood against facism, all while maintaining households and duties outside of their normal realm.

title: Protect Social Security Rally
description:
Join us as we rally to protect Social Security!

Sponsored by Michigan Families for Fair Care and Bee Accepting, we believe it is critical to rally around Social Security and remind Congressman Tom Barrett and the Trump administration of how vital the program is to millions of Americans - including those in Michigan's 7th Congressional District.

Snacks and refreshments will be provided at the event. Be sure to bring your signs if you have one, otherwise we'll have materials made available for you to put one together!

title: Fight for Our Madera County Schools
description:
We will gather at the Oakhurst Library May 17 to show our objection to Federal funding cuts to our local Madera County schools! 

14.7 million dollars in special education funds will be cut from Madera County schools!
51.7 million total funding loss for  Madera County Schools!

We will park at Oakhurst Library at 11:30, listen to speakers and have chant practice there, then march to Rite Aid corner to rally in support of our Madera County schools! 
Let‚Äôs do this!

Please DO NOT park in the Rite Aid Lot. There is parking at the Oakhurst Library. We will set up transportation to the Rite aid corner for those with mobility issues.

Sign up at Yosemiteaction.org to be notified of future Oakhurst events.
We are not an organization. If you choose to join us at any event that we announce, it is as an individual citizen, not as a member of any group.
accessibility_notes:
Transport is being organized to shuttle people with mobility issues from the Oakhurst library parking lot to the Rally on the
Corner in front of Rite Aid.
Please do not park in the Rite Aid parking lot or owner will tow.

title: "Moral Monday" Street Rally

address_lines: N. Main St. and W. Division St.

description:
Please join us in opposing cuts to essential safety net programs!

Please join us at weekly recurring  "Moral Monday" street rallies, alternating between Hudson WI and River Falls WI.

Our first ‚ÄúMoral Monday‚Äù street rally will be in Downtown Hudson on Monday May 5, from 4PM to 6PM, at the intersection of Second and Vine Streets, where we will hold signs and stand along the public sidewalks.

Our second ‚ÄúMoral Monday‚Äù street rally will be in River Falls on Monday May 12, from 4PM to 6PM, at the intersection of Main and Division Streets, where we will hold signs and stand along the public sidewalks.

Folks may join for part or all the two hours, and may bring their own signs or use signs we‚Äôll have to share.

If the weather is bad‚Äîhard rain, high wind, and/or lightening‚Äîwe‚Äôll cancel that week‚Äôs rally.

Our "Moral Monday" street rallies are inspired and informed by work of the prominent North Carolina pastor and anti-poverty activist the Rev. William Barber, who founded the Center for Public Theology and Public Policy at Yale and now teaches there.

On the twelfth anniversary of his first "Moral Monday" demonstration, Monday April 28, 2025, Rev. Barber was arrested for praying against the Republican-led budget while in the Rotunda of our US Capitol. At a rally held before he entered the Rotunda to pray, Rev. Barber said: ‚ÄúForty-three percent of women and almost half of all children are poor and low income. Somebody ought to say something ‚Ä¶ Somebody gotta challenge this budget.‚Äù

We are holding "Moral Monday" street rallies to voice our challenges.

We oppose Republican-approved Congressional budget resolutions that harm the poorest and most vulnerable of Americans in order to give more than $5-trillion in tax breaks to the richest and most privileged of Americans.

We oppose Trump/Musk budget proposals that eliminate or make draconian cuts to federal programs for child care, health research, education, housing assistance, community development, and the elderly.

These funding cuts and proposed budgets are not just public policy choices, they are moral choices. 

These funding cuts and proposed budgets are morally wrong, not just bad public policy choices. 

Please join with us to "say something" and "challenge this budget".

title: Fri. 5/16 > Mass Pike Overpass Standout - Southampton Rd (Routes 10/202), Westfield
description:
Wow! What a great location for a standout! A few of us tried it out on Friday, May 2. There's a full-size sidewalk on the west side, and a narrow sidewalk (kind of like the narrow sidewalk at Mountain Park Rd.) on the east side. The west side will accommodate more people than the east side.

There's lots and lots of traffic passing by. Southampton Road (Routes 10/202) is heavily traveled northbound and southbound, and the Mass Pike eastbound and westbound is below. Lots of honks and thumbs up and waves...and a few folks flying middle fingers. We smile and wave at them all! 

We'll have letterboards prepared for the lower part of the overpass fencing - the photo shows how that will look to folks passing on the Mass Pike. We're interacting with motorists on the Mass Pike, and on Southampton Road. We've discovered that the magic happens when we smile and wave to people!

Come when you can, and leave when you must. You needn't be present for the entire 2-hour standout.

### How to Get There

The address "130 Southampton Road, Westfield" will get you just north of the overpass. 

### Parking

We can't park in the Southampton Rd breakdown lane. There's a vacant business property three or four properties north of the bridge, and it seems that parking would be OK there.

It looks like The Wealth Technology Group has vacated their office at 130 Southampton Rd, but the internet says that other businesses are located there, so please be mindful if you decide to park there.

### Etiquette!

We don't give the finger to people who give the finger to us, or who say unpleasant things. We smile and wave to them, too. 

We may see a counter protester. If so, the best thing to do is just ignore them and spend our time and energy waving to motorists. Let's keep things 100% non-confrontational in words and body language.

### Other Stuff

Please take everything you brought away with you, and leave the site totally clean.

If rain is predicted, we'll cancel. If we cancel, you'll receive an email notification.

### A Few Requests

We've found that roof rake sections make wonderful flagpoles and banner poles. If you have a roof rake (or 10‚Äô-15‚Äô light metal poles or conduit) to contribute, we'll be happy to take it off your hands!

Donations...we've purchased banners and grommets and flags and zip ties and bungee cords, and we'll be getting more. We‚Äôve purchased 20‚Äù x 30‚Äù letter boards for messaging we can change. All this costs $$$. We'll have a bucket for donations, and if you could throw something in, that'd be great. And if not, that's perfectly OK, too - your presence is what's really important. See where the money's going! https://tinyurl.com/IN-SLWMProtestTeamFinancials

description:
Join tens of thousands of your fellow Chicago-area citizens as we form a human chain of conscience across Chicagoland in peaceful protest against Trump‚Äôs illegal and authoritarian actions and the GOP's failure to defend the Constitution.

We will line sidewalks along 30 miles from Aurora to Chicago along Ogden Ave, 26th Street and California Ave to Douglass Park. This is a peaceful protest. We will not block streets or businesses along the route.

Bring signs, wear black, and make some noise.

Find and reserve your spot here: www.handsacrosschi.com

Using the website widget will help us spread people out evenly along the route, while keeping people close to where they live.

President Trump has defied court orders and forcibly sent people to a torture dungeon in El Salvador without a hearing or due process. Now he claims he‚Äôs unable to bring them back. He's ignored court rulings and arrested judges. If he can do this to them, he can do it to anyone.

These are the actions of a dictator‚Äînot a democratically elected president. Silence is not an option. When leaders cross the line into authoritarianism, it‚Äôs up to us‚Äîthe people‚Äîto push back. This protest is about more than politics. It's about defending basic human dignity, civil liberties, and the idea that no one is above the law.

description:

Hands off our rights! Hands off our people! Hands off free speech! Hands off LGBTQ+ rights! Hands off due process! Hands off union and workers! Hands off working families! Hands off Medicaid/Medicare! Hands off education! Hands off diversity, equity and inclusion! 

During this event, there will be a public reading of the Constitution by members of the public and invited speakers. Please RSVP for more information.

Thanks!

TRANSPORTATION AND PARKING:

Parking near The Green is limited, so you may prefer to walk or take transit. If you can, consider public transit:

East Norwalk Metro North station is a 20-minute walk to the Town Green.

Norwalk Transit District runs frequent bus service from the Greater Norwalk area to Burnell Blvd, a short walk from the Town Green:

- From Flax Hill or Hospital Hill, take the WHEELs 9 on Fairfield Ave or 
   Stevens St.
- From East Norwalk, take the WHEELs 11 from Van Zant Street or East Ave,
   or the WHEELs 7 from Westport Ave or Strawberry Hill Ave.
- From Merritt 7 or Main Ave area, take the WHEELs 3 on Main Ave or 
  Glover Ave.
- From other parts of Norwalk, you can take Wheels2U 
  (https://www.wheels2u.org/) starting at 1 PM.


Parking: 

Please park at either:
Yankee Doodle Garage, Norwalk
or Norwalk City Hall

Both of these are a 10-15 minute walk to the Green.

Please only park on the side streets near the Town Green if you have an accessible parking permit! We're trying to keep the protest as inclusive as we can!

Please email goodtroublenorwalk@gmail.com for additional accessibility information.

title: Tesla Takedown - Stanford Mall
description:
CALSTRS and CALPERS: Divest from Tesla Funds NOW!

City of Palo Alto: Divest from Tesla Funds NOW!

STOP THE BILLIONAIRE TAKEOVER. WE ARE THE MANY. THEY ARE THE FEW. JOIN US.

We know making lots of noise is typically part of a good protest. But most protests aren‚Äôt right across the street from a Ronald McDonald House. Let‚Äôs take care to keep our noise levels down to a dull roar. Bring your energy and spirit, but let‚Äôs ditch the cowbells, drums and car honks. Do not boo or confront Tesla drivers or cars, or Tesla employees. Remember that most Tesla drivers are our allies, and many are protesting with us!

No one voted for Musk. Join the peaceful Tesla Takedown movement!

In solidarity, please add #LatinoFreeze or #LatinoFreezeMovement to placards.

Free Ulises, Free Kilmar, Free Khalil. Free them all! 

Elon Musk is destroying our democracy, and he's using the fortune he built at Tesla to do it. We are taking nonviolent action at Tesla to stop Musk's illegal coup.

‚ö°Sell your Teslas, dump your stock, join the picket lines.

‚ö° We're tanking Tesla's stock price to stop Musk.

‚ö°Stopping Musk will help save lives and protect our democracy.

The stakes couldn‚Äôt be higher. No one is coming to save us. Not politicians, not the media, not the courts.

Tesla Takedown is a peaceful protest movement. We oppose violence, vandalism and destruction of property. This protest is a lawful exercise of our First Amendment right to peaceful assembly.

#TeslaTakedown #BoycottTesla #DueProcess #LatinoFreeze

title: Protect NY's Climate Law - Syracuse
description:
Join Citizen Action of NY, PUSH Buffalo, NY Renews, Third Act Upstate New York, and local CNY groups to rally and testify at a DEC public hearing in Syracuse on June 3 at noon to defend NY‚Äôs Climate Law.

New Yorkers will join to voice their support for climate leadership and to urge Governor Hochul to stand up to Trump by funding climate legislation. Join us and help make this impactful by emailing egormley@citizenactionny.org.

The climate change-denier in the White House is doing everything he can to eliminate climate progress in this country. We need climate leadership in NY, and we need it now. Unfortunately, in January, Governor Hochul revealed that she‚Äôs delaying a crucial component of the state‚Äôs Climate Law called Cap and Invest. 


Cap and Invest is an emissions-reduction program that would limit, or cap, emissions from major polluters in the state. That cap would tighten over time, gradually reducing the amount of emissions allowed for release. Meanwhile, major polluters will have to pay to release polluting emissions up to the level of the cap. Those funds from polluters will then be used to invest in green energy, jobs, home decarbonization programs, and similar efforts to support NY communities.

To move Cap and Invest forward, we need the Department of Environmental Conservation (DEC) to release three sets of regulations that hold polluters accountable to Cap and Invest. Unfortunately, Governor Hochul has  released only one.

title: Roswell Empowered Alive After 5 Sidewalk Protest
description:
We had our first successful rally in Roswell on 5/3‚Äìlet‚Äôs keep up the momentum. Empower Roswell, Ignite Change. This is only the spark!

Roswell may be a small city just outside of Atlanta, but our voices are big. Our voices matter.

It‚Äôs important for our leaders‚Äîboth local and state-wide‚Äîto know and understand that people all across this country, this state, this city‚Äîthe city of Roswell‚Äîare not going to accept the reckless agenda of the current administration.

Regardless of political affiliation, we all know that deep down what has been happening is not ok. And we want our leaders‚Äîregardless of political affiliation to hold this administration accountable.

We want leaders who will fight for the futures of our families, not those concerned only about their fortunes.

We want leaders who will stand up and fight for our schools and ensure our children have access to quality education, not those who want to erase history and rip away programs designed to help students that need it the most. We want leaders who will protect our neighbors, not those who spread fear and hateful rhetoric and seek to eliminate diversity in our communities.

We want leaders who will fight for our rights, fight for democracy, not those who promote corruption, oligarchy and tyranny.

We want leaders who will protect healthcare including Medicare, Medicaid, and affordable treatment and prescriptions, not those who seek to pull the rug out from the most vulnerable members of our communities‚Äîveterans, the elderly, those will special needs, the sick, the impoverished.
We want leaders who lead by example, not those who sell their own Bible, but exemplify the opposite of its contents.

We want our leaders‚Äîlocal and nationwide‚Äîto hear us and take action against Trump and his corrupt billionaire buddies. And that action starts here, in Roswell, GA.

A peaceful sidewalk protest on both sides of Atlanta St between Magnolia and Norcross Streets‚Äîparallel to the Alive After 5 event on Canton St.

Please remain on the sidewalk, no signs that say ‚Äúhonk‚Äù, follow all local laws.

This event will be rain or shine.
Parking gets tight‚Äîplease make a plan to carpool, park in one of the local churches, or find paid parking (I know that‚Äôs not ideal, but make sure if you do park in a paid lot you pay‚Äîtypically by phone‚Äîwe don‚Äôt want anyone getting towed).

Thank you for your support and look forward to seeing you there!
Roswell Empowered: Empower Roswell, Ignite Change

title: Stand Up / Speak Out Rally in Hudson
description:
Stand Up/Speak Out is holding a rally in Hudson on May 25 in response to the ongoing cuts to the federal workforce and services that support veterans, Social Security beneficiaries, and healthcare providers and patients in New York. The event hopes to encourage local citizens to gather, learn from one another, and sound the alarm that no one is safe in an America that has turned its back on its veterans, the elderly, and the ability of millions to access healthcare. 

Our speaker lineup so far includes Andrea Goldstein, a veteran and a former staffer of the House Committee on Veterans Affairs; Rennie Glasgow, Vice President of the American Federation of Government Employees (AFGE ), Local 3343; and Ashley Fox, MA, PhD, a public policy and global health policy expert. In addition, we will hear from folks directly impacted by the current and anticipated federal cuts to the Veterans Administration, Social Security, and government healthcare programs, including Medicaid.

Come join in! Bring your signs and your friends!

description: This is a local Indivisible event! Join us with your signs to tell Rep. Chris Smith what you think of how he represents us down in Washington.  Let him know if you think he is voting in your best interest! 12-1 Tuesday, May 13th at 33 Washington Street, Toms River.

title: Protest the Trump Administration!
description:
Please join us as we protest the Republican Federal Administration! A top administration official (reportedly Kristi Noem, U.S. Secretary of Homeland Security, but this will soon be confirmed) will speak at the U.S. Coast Guard Graduation.  

Wednesday, May 21st
8:30-10:30
Location: McKinley Park
Corner of Williams St and Mohegan Ave in New London, CT

Democracy belongs to all of us‚Äînot to dictators, kings, dynasties, billionaires or those who seek to hoard power and accumulate wealth for the 1%. Join us for a peaceful, high-energy rally where we‚Äôll stand together for free and fair elections, equal representation, and government by the people, for the people!

Our message: we do not consent to the destruction of our government and our economy for the benefit of Trump and his billionaire allies. We are marching, rallying, and protesting to demand a stop the chaos and build an opposition movement against the looting of our country.

We have no quarrel with the cadets or individuals who engage in a military career. We are here to tell the administration: RESTORE services for immigrants, education, veterans, students, the elderly, parents, children, the disabled or disadvantaged; and Hands OFF social security

One of our core principles is a commitment to nonviolent action. We expect all participants to seek to de-escalate any potential confrontation with those who disagree with our values.

Sponsored by the Unify & Resist Coalition, including Indivisible Southeast CT

title: Laws Matter: Standing in Solidarity with the Judicial System
description:
This Honk and Wave and Food Drive will be held at Lafayette Park in Watkins Glen.  We are working with the local Democratic Party on this. We will stand to support our Judicial System.  The current administration often ignores important court rulings as well as our Constitution at times. Some Executive Orders have been declared unconstitutional but their rulings seem to fall on deaf ears. We need to remind our representatives that LAWS MATTER. They should NOT be ignored! They protect our safety, our rights, and our ability to live in our communities in PEACE. Now is the time to support our courts and judges as well as express our distress when their rulings are ignored or the judges, themselves, are threatened. Bring your sign and your voice! 

We will gather on the sidwalk along Fourth Street and around the corner on Decatur.  

PLEASE BE RESPECTFUL OF THE PRIVATE RESIDENCES.  DO NOT STAND IN FRONT OF OUR NEIGHBORS' HOMES.  

PLEASE CARPOOL TO SAVE PARKING PLACES. PARKING IS ON THE STREET ONLY.

We will be having a food drive. Please bring a non-perishable food item to share with a local food bank.
accessibility_notes: Please carpool

title: D-Day Protest - June 6 - Longview

location.venue: On The Border Mexican Grill & Cantina

description: June 6th, 1944 D-Day, was a turning point in history. Allied troops stormed the beaches of Normandy to fight back against fascism. For veterans, it's a reminder of the cost of defending freedom and democracy. Honoring this day means recognizing their sacrifice and the values they stood for.

title: Bridge Rally to Defend Democracy

location.venue: Highway 12 Bridge, across from Kwik Trip

description:
Gather with friends and neighbors for a protest to stop the Republican dismantling of our democracy held on the Highway 12 bridge in Sauk City. 

Join Indivisible Sauk Prairie as we stand for our democracy, the rule of law, due process and real, true American values. 

Bring American flags and family-friendly signs. We will also be collecting non-perishable food for the Sauk Prairie Food Pantry. 

This is a non-violent and non-confrontational event. We have a lot of fun and feel free to join us for any amount of time!

title: Hands Across Chicagoland
description:
Join tens of thousands of your fellow Chicago-area citizens, along with Western Kane Democrats, Dupage Democrats, Batavia Township Democrats, St. Charles Township Democrats, Indivisible Fox Valley Rising, and We Can Lead Change - we will form a human chain of conscience across Chicaoland in peaceful protest against Trump's illegal and authoritarian actions and the GOP's failure to defned the Constitution.

Bring signs, wear black, and make some noise.

We will line sidewalks along 30 miles from Aurora to Chicago along Ogden Ave, 26th Street, and California Ave. to Douglass Park.  This is a peaceful protest.  We will not block streets or businesses along the route.

Please go to www.handsacrosschi.com and enter your zip code to get an assigned location along the route.  This is important so that we can spread people out evenly along the route, while keeping people closer to where they live.

title: CD 3 - KILEY - Save Mercy Hospital from Medicaid Cuts!
description:
The Republican led Congress is proposing to make devastating cuts to healthcare programs which could impact 15 million Californians, including children and people with disabilities!  And they're making the cuts to give huge tax breaks to millionaires and billionaires.

Many hospitals around the state could lose major funding. Mercy Hospital could lose millions of dollars.  The proposed cuts would mean devastating cutbacks in services and longer wait times - even for people who have private insurance.  

To stop the cuts and save lives we need to get a handful of Republican Congressmembers to vote NO on the proposed healthcare cuts.  We'll be rallying to save Mercy Hospital in Folsom on Tuesday, May 13th at 11:30 AM with doctors, nurses, other healthcare providers and community supporters to call on Congressman Kevin Kiley to vote NO on any cuts to Medicaid!

We have **NO KINGS** here in America. And, _*we won't tolerate*_ a president who acts like one. So, join us at Alameda City Hall on Saturday June 14th from 12 noon till 1 PM to make our voices heard.

Also, we will have a food donation bin at the protest site in support of our neighbors in need. Please bring non-perishable food items for donation. Every little bit helps! Look for more details to be included in upcoming email updates to registered attendees.

Your presence will be appreciated by everyone! Thanks in advance.
accessibility_notes: This event location is the public plaza in front of Alameda City Hall. The plaza is a flat, paved area. There are a few benches at the location, but if you cannot stand for the duration of your time at the protest, you are welcome to bring a lawn chair or camp chair. Just make sure to set your chair up in an area off to the side, not in the middle, for safety reasons. There is an adjacent bus stop. The closest bathroom facilities are located at the Alameda Free Library at 1550 Oak St (a block away on an adjacent street). Parking will be scarce. Please use ride-sharing or public transit.

title: No Kings
description:
Indivisible: Heart of the Ozarks will be joining the National Day of Protest to declare on Flag Day that we don't want a King. 

Trump is planning a multi-million dollar Military Parade for his birthday on June 14th. We must show how disrespectful this is to the Military and every US Citizen. No King - No Dictator

Bring a Friend or two. We have to keep the momentum going.
I will bring blank poster board and markers to make your own signs if needed. Please no foul language and keep the message to the issues.

All Rallies will be held in West Plains Missouri at the corner of Hwy 63 and 160 near Ruby Tuesday.

Be safe and stay back from the curb. Do not block the sight lines for cars turning off 63 onto 160.
Do not take up the parking places for any of the businesses. In fact, if you can be a customer that would be great.

title: Join DeKalb Dems at Juneteenth in Stonecrest
description:
The City of Stonecrest is celebrating Juneteenth bigger than ever before this year by hosting it's 3rd annual Juneteenth Celebration of Freedom on Saturday June 14, 2025.

DeKalb Dems will have a visibility tent and we need volunteers to assist with set up and act as Ambassadors who listen to citizen's concerns, offer ways we can support them, and talk about what they can do to safeguard our freedom.

Juneteenth commemorates the effective end of slavery in the United States. Two years after President Lincoln signed the Emancipation Proclamation, news reached Texas and, upon learning they were free, former slaves immediately began celebrating with prayer, feasting, song, and dance. The Juneteenth Celebration of Freedom will celebrate African American culture, heritage, and, most importantly, abolishment of slavery.

The Juneteenth Celebration of Freedom will feature an expanded kidz zone, live performances, food trucks, vendors, and fireworks show. It is a place for all races, nationalities, and religions to join hands and truthfully acknowledge a period in history that shaped and continues to influence our society today, according to a news release. This event is free and open to the public, and we encourage everyone to attend and learn more about the history and culture of Juneteenth!

Please sign up for a shift below and be a part of this Celebration of Freedom.

title: Democratic Visibility Rally
description:
Join the Democratic Party of Chippewa County, Chippewa Valley Indivisible, and other citizen action groups to rally for DEMOCRACY! Come to the roundabout on N Bridge St with your signs to let everyone know we are standing up for democracy! Let's get the movement growing! 

Take a stand against the President's unlawful and unconstitutional actions. Take a stand for protecting Social Security, Medicaid, federal agencies, national parks, due process, rule of law, the environment, and more. Stand for our democracy, for our families, friends, and neighbors. Get your signs ready and come let the community know this matters to you!

There's no such thing as bad weather, just bad clothing choices! Dress for Rally Success! Let's gather together and speak up for our children, grandchildren, and our community!

There are two public parking lots on Bridge and River Streets.

title: #TeslaTakedown Baltimore
description:
Elon Musk is destroying our democracy, and he's using the fortune he built at Tesla to do it. We are taking nonviolent action at Tesla to stop Musk's illegal coup.

The stakes couldn‚Äôt be higher. No one is coming to save us. Not politicians, not the media, not the courts.

Tesla Takedown is a peaceful protest movement. We oppose violence, vandalism and destruction of property. This protest is a lawful exercise of our First Amendment right to peaceful assembly.

#TeslaTakedown

IMPORTANT PARKING INFORMATION: Don't risk being towed from the Dunkin parking lot! Please park in the unmarked lots on Park Center Ct - the first right after turning on Crossroads Dr. From there, you can walk up the hill behind NTB and through the parking lot to the Tesla driveway corner.
accessibility_notes: We have folks join us each week with limited mobility or accessibility requirements. Many opt to be dropped off in the NTB/Dunkin parking area, then their companion can park the car on Center Point Dr. We assemble on the sidewalk, which is mostly flat, but please use caution at curbs and uneven areas.

title: Protect our Neighbors
description:
From our elected judges to our immigrant community, our neighbors are under attack. The current administration had openly declared a disregard for due process, constitutional law, and other critical components of America.

Despite this, many Americans have not stepped up into any type of defiance against this administration. Join us on May 17th to communicate a clear message: America, protect our neighbors.

Invite anyone and everyone that you can, and bring signs that encourage others to protect their neighbor.

We will start our rally at Tenney Park, then we will march around a mile and a half. Be prepared to stand for extended periods (or bring a foldable chair.)

Whose streets? Our streets?

title: Pro Democracy Protest
description:
This a local Upper Valley Indivisible event!

Our democracy is under threat. But we will not yield to fascism. We will stand together and we'll fight back in defense of our rights, our communities, and our values.

Join us Thursdays from 5-5:45 pm to protest at the Lebanon green/Colburn Park.

PLEASE NOTE WE ARE SHIFTING OUR LOCATION TO THE OPPOSITE SIDE OF THE GREEN STARTING MAY 15th THE FARMERS MARKET IS STARTING THIS DAY. More information to follow for that date.

We will gather on the sidewalk outside of the green space, near the Upper Valley Music Center and post office side of Colburn park. Our permit does not allow us to be in the street, in empty parking spots, on the green, or on the sidewalk near the bus stop. Please allow plenty of room for pedestrians to move through freely. Bring your sign, and if you have extra, bring those too. Some folks might show up without one, or someone may walk by and spontaneously want to join us.

title: Stand Up for Justice* Equity * Democracy Rally and Food Drive May 17th!

location.venue: Castillo de San Marcos National Monument

description:
We are standing up to protest the Trump administration for:
-Defying and intimidating our justices and legal system!
-Treating people like rodents to be eliminated, Taking their personal belongings including their cash, trashing their homes, locking them up without due process, shipping them out of the country 
-Trashing the rights of our LGBTQ+ community
-Slashing jobs that are vital to the welfare of our country
-Slashing federal jobs; Veterans fill 1/3 of all federal jobs
-And as everyone says: Too Many Things to List Here!!

THANK YOU!

title: ITC Defend Veterans
description:
Join us on Thursday, May 22 at 4pm for our next ITC Defend America's Essentials Rally Series: we'll be standing up to Defend Veterans.

We are rallying to support all veterans and oppose the Trump regime's efforts to slash the federal workforce, including cutting 83,000 VA jobs gutting veterans' health care and research, along with severely reducing staffing for the Veterans Crisis Line, a suicide hotline.

Whether they were deployed abroad or assigned to posts in the U.S. in war or peacetime, veterans protected our country. Now, all of us need show up and defend our veterans.

title: Bannering 101 : RESIST !
description:
High Visibility Bannering Opportunity over Hwy 101 
Bannering is an effective way to get our message out, and inspire and support others.  At 20,000 VPH peak traffic multiplied by four locations on four days we have a chance to connect over 750,000 times.   

Location 1: Ralston in Belmont
 
Location:        
O'Neill bike ped bridge  (near Ralston)  Belmont 12 noon to 2pm 
Exit Ralston / Marine Parkway -> Belmont Sports and Conference Center
Parking:          
Park at the baseball field behind the Mercedes dealership
https://maps.app.goo.gl/aef6CCTPDhU73qMP8

Walk north, past the large building and the baseball diamond to the overpass. You may also be able to access via Hiller Street.

 
Setup:
The letters on this batch are 36" tall with a horizontal reach of 14'.   We will have the RESIST banner as well as 86 47.   I  am bringing banners, tools, supplies, and a step ladder.  I am bringing two American flags (to be flown upside down, in distress). Any large signs you have can be held up and waved.

Plan ahead:    
Bring ear protection, sunscreen, dress warmly, expect gusts up to 20 MPH.  Bring large signs!  Contact me for blank signs.

title: NO KINGS Raleigh
description:
This June 14th, stand with us at the steps of the North Carolina State Capitol for No Kings Day‚Äîa nonpartisan, peaceful rally in defense of the American principles we all hold dear: democracy, accountability, and the rule of law.

Across the political spectrum, more and more Americans are feeling disillusioned by leaders who put themselves above the people. This day is for anyone who believes that no one‚Äîno matter how powerful‚Äîshould be treated like royalty in a nation built on liberty.

We‚Äôre gathering not in anger, but in unity. This is a space for reflection, connection, and a shared commitment to a country where leaders serve, not rule. Whether you're conservative, progressive, independent, or politically unsure‚Äîif you believe in the idea of a government by and for the people, this rally is for you.

This is a peaceful, de-escalation-focused event. There is no place here for violence, intimidation, or hate. We welcome calm, respectful voices who want to help shape a future rooted in mutual respect and civic responsibility.

Bring your signs, your friends, your conscience‚Äîand your belief that the United States was never meant to have kings.

title: No Kings On D-Day
description:
# On June 6th, 2025, the Anniversary of D-Day, Mass 50501 will hold an event in remembrance of our heroes in uniform, past and present.

Our mission is the preservation of the democracy that they fought‚Äîand in some cases died‚Äîto protect on the shores of Europe. We will feature speakers who are themselves veterans, who will speak on history, duty, honor, sacrifice, and patriotism. We will conduct a wreath-laying ceremony at the Soldiers and Sailors Monument on the Boston Common featuring patriotic renditions of ‚ÄúTaps,‚Äù ‚ÄúBattle Hymn of the Republic,‚Äù and other songs. We will protest cuts to the VA, oppose the undemocratic way in which the administration has treated its duties, reaffirm our support for our allies, and recommit ourselves to the principles that have governed the nation and its military for centuries, and we will remind the people that veterans and active duty military personnel exist to protect the nation against all enemies, foreign and domestic. It will be both a protest and a solemn event of remembrance. 

## Event Program

## Act 1: Invocation of Service
An honor guard procession will bear American, State, and Service flags from the Soldiers and Sailors Monument to the stage, followed by an invocation and remarks from the Program Director. 

## Act 2: The Citizen Soldier
We'll hear from ordinary citizens‚Äîveterans and those who support them‚Äîaddressing the issues that matter to veterans today.

## Act 3: A Call to Duty
VIP speakers will offer stories to help draw us together, and remind us that the bonds of service do not end upon separation from the military and that participation in our democracy is essential to its health and prosperity.

## Act 4: Honor the Fallen
The honor guard and key speakers will process back to the Soldiers and Sailors Monument to lay a wreath, followed by Taps, a moment of silence, and closing words. 

# Flags are welcome, but please leave protest signs at home.

Organizer and strategist Daniel Hunter has written that ‚ÄúHumor is important for our psyches ‚Äî and to take fascists down a notch[‚Ä¶] Humor is key for morale and exposing the vulnerability of the strongman image.‚Äù This is where the ridiculous meets the resistance‚Äîand where the future is on the line.

June 14 is our chance to reflect the absurdity of the MAGA regime and the clowns who lead it. To meet this moment, Women‚Äôs March will host community circuses nationwide‚Äîbold, creative actions that mirror the chaos MAGA has sown across the country. Together, we‚Äôll set a national record for the most circuses held in a single day while we simultaneously refuse to celebrate a petty clown who desperately wants to be seen as strong. We won‚Äôt stop until we build the country we all deserve.

title: No Cake for False Kings
description:
üóìÔ∏è June 14, 2025
üïê 1:00‚Äì4:00 PM
üìç 17th Street NW Bridge, over Atlanta highways (near Atlantic Station)

On June 14th, while Donald Trump attempts to display military power meant to silence dissent, we will rise above the noise‚Äîliterally and symbolically.

No Cake for False Kings is a high-visibility, nonviolent protest that will take place on the 17th Street NW pedestrian bridge, which crosses over ALL of Atlanta‚Äôs busiest highways. We are joining activists across America to send one unified message: we reject authoritarianism, abuse of power, and the erasure of our rights.

This is not a celebration. This is a warning.
There will be no cake, no crowns, and no complicity.

üî• What to Expect:
- A powerful visual presence over the highway with large protest banners

- Protesters lining both sides of the bridge sidewalks to reach drivers below and pedestrians around

- Organized chants, signs, and nonviolent resistance

- An Information & Resource Table with know-your-rights guides, activist materials, and ways to plug in

- A Water & Cooling Station to ensure safety in the heat

** Participants are strongly encouraged to WEAR RED as a unified symbol of protest and defiance. 

üéíWhat to bring: 
- For those wanting to avoid the summer sun, having an umbrella to provide shade is encouraged. 

- Wear a hat, sunglasses, and sunscreen to protect from the sun!

- Water, water, water! We will have a water station as well as cooling towels and packs, but these are limited, so bring water for yourself and your group if possible.

- Signs and flags are strongly encouraged, but organizers will have extras for those in need *limited, first come first serve 

- Foldable chair: for those needing a break from standing for long periods of time

-Snacks: protesting takes energy, so bring some snacks to refuel! 


üß≠ Getting There:
-Parking is available at Atlantic Station just steps away from the bridge

- For those using public transit, MARTA‚Äôs Arts Center Station is the closest stop and offers a shuttle to Atlantic Station

This protest is about visibility and truth. We must be loud, proud, and impossible to ignore. Bring your voice, your signs, and your conviction.

Together, we will show this country that we do not bow to tyrants‚Äîwe rise up against them.

Please consider donating to fund permit costs as well as event items! 

Donations can be accepted at this link: https://gofund.me/680f382b

Anything truly helps when fighting for Democracy, & we couldn't do it without our wonderful community <3

title: Hands Off Medicaid Rally!
description:
Drastic cuts to the federal budget are underway and we are standing up to say:

Hands Off Medicaid!

1.2 million Minnesotans rely on Medicaid (aka Medical Assistance) in some way. Proposed cuts to Medicaid are estimated to cost Minnesotans up to $1.6 Billion per year in federal funds.

AFSCME Local 34 workers provide social services to the residents of Hennepin County, many of whom rely on Medicaid. We stand firmly against any cuts to healthcare benefits for our residents or anyone else for that matter.

We cannot afford cuts to Medicaid - join us at the Paul D Wellstone Federal Building on Tuesday, May 13th at 12pm and make your voice heard!
accessibility_notes: This event will take place outside the building on the sidewalk, this building is open to the public for restroom use.

title: #NoKings Day with Sister District Project SF
description:
Join your friends and neighbors at Sister District Project San Francisco for the #NoKings mass protest and day of defiance!

On June 14, rise up with millions across the country, on Tr*mp's planned military parade day, to stand in opposition and fight back against the attacks on our freedoms by this jury-determined rapist, twice-impeached, 34-time convicted felon, and January 6 traitor. 

Look for the Sister District San Francisco banner in front of 350 McAllister between Larkin & Polk from 10:30 ‚Äì 11am before we head to the main rally in front of City Hall. 

Bring signs, wear your SDP t-shirt and caps if you have them (we'll have a few extras). 

Together, let's demand a country that puts our families over billionaires' fortunes‚Äîpublic schools over private profits, healthcare over hedge funds, prosperity over the profits of price-gouging and climate polluting corporations.

_A core principle behind all #NoKings events is a commitment to nonviolent action. We expect all participants to seek to de-escalate any potential confrontation with those who disagree with our values._

To learn more about this national day of action, visit [nokings.org](https://www.nokings.org/)

To learn more about Sister District Project, visit [SisterDistrict.com](https://sisterdistrict.com/strategy).

Since 2016, Sister District Project has been building enduring progressive power in the states to improve people's lives, including by supporting community-based organizations led by people of color on the ground, like [New Virginia Majority](https://secure.actblue.com/donate/sd016-va-nvmef-sf), who do critical grassroots work year round.

You are welcome to join any of our monthly meetings, whichever is most convenient for you! 

We host events on **Zoom the first Tuesday** of each month; in-person **Happy Hours on the first Thursdays** of even-numbered months; in-person **Coffee Hours on first Thursdays** of odd-numbered months (locations vary); or in-person **Postcard events** on third Sundays or Mondays.

title: Stand for Immigrant Rights and Due Process for All
description:
Join us May 17th in front of Lakewood City Hall to protest the abhorrent and abusive acts the current administration has taken towards our fellow humans. We are here to protect our neighbors and use our voices for those that cannot. We are here to gather in community to show solidarity to our immigrant communities and to raise awareness of the unlawful and unconstitutional acts of the White House. 

Immigrants have rights! Due process for all! No human is illegal!

title: SEIU Michigan Corrections Organization Constitutional Rally
description: State Corrections Officers and partners are holding a rally to demand accountability and integrity from our elected officials. The Michigan Constitution is being undermined by the deliberate obstruction of critical legislation--bills that were lawfully passed by both chambers of the legislature last year and are now being intentionally withheld.

title: No to Elon, Yes to Government by the People
description:
This is Upper Merion Indivisible! Elon Musk's seizing control of the US Government needs to be stopped. We need to stand up and let the world know how we feel.

We're leading a nonviolent rally outside of the Upper Merion/King of Prussia Tesla Collision/Repair building to let the community know supporting Tesla is bad for democracy, and to remind our entire community that Elon's lawless actions are dangerous and won't be tolerated.

This is a peaceful action. We will not enter the business, nor stop people from entering or exiting the property. No violence or threats against anyone will be tolerated.

Bring your own signs encouraging people to honk for democracy and sharing your thoughts about Elon's wrecking of our government. Let's show the world that we won't tolerate his threat to government of the people, by the people, and for the people.

Nearby on-street parking is available.

title: Protest Avelo Airlines' Plan to Carry Out Deportation Flights - ONGOING
description:
This is a local Indivisible event!

Avelo Airlines has accepted a $150 million contract to operate deportation flights, aiding in the illegal removal of individuals without their right to a fair hearing or due process. This is not only inhumane but a direct violation of our Constitution.

We‚Äôre calling for a full boycott of Avelo Airlines and organizing weekly protests at our local airport.

We will be on the sidewalk leading to the Charles M. Schulz Sonoma County Airport, which is currently a hub for Avelo's flights. At a time when a maximum number of travelers will see our protest, it is also a good opportunity to protest federal layoffs with the FAA.

You can park nearby or take SMART to get there.

title: Speak Out, Seniors! Stand Out/Sit Out for Democracy

address_lines: Beacon Street & Harvard Street, Brookline, MA 02446

description:
Join us for a Stand out/Sit out rally especially for seniors‚Äîbut open to all ages‚Äîat Coolidge Corner! We‚Äôre speaking out against the abuses of the Trump administration.  Let‚Äôs stand up for many things: immigrant rights and human rights; free speech, the Constitution and the rule of law; healthcare and social security; and the health of our planet.  We stand up for democracy, justice, and the future we want to leave to the next generation.

This is a peaceful, spirited gathering‚Äîbring your voice, your friends, and your signs! Walkers, wheelchairs, scooters, and all mobility devices are welcome.

Suggestion:  bring a water bottle.

In case of bad weather, organizers may not be present‚Äîbut anyone who wishes to come is, of course, welcome to do so.

Let‚Äôs show the world that seniors will not be silent!  Speak Out, Seniors! is building power, one rally at a time.  Let‚Äôs start a weekly tradition!

Join us for the We Love Our VA Rally, a peaceful, nonpartisan gathering to show unwavering support for our veterans and the dedicated VA healthcare professionals and support staff who serve them every day.

RSVP now and bring a friend. Let‚Äôs rally for those who‚Äôve given so much.

title: Croton, NY: Pass a Resolution Against Project Maple
description:
**Join us outside the Croton Board of Trustees meeting to demand local action against Project Maple** ‚Äî a dangerous fracked gas pipeline expansion plan that threatens our climate, our river, and our health.

Fossil Fuel company Enbridge's Project Maple would expand the amount of fracked gas running through the existing Algonquin Pipeline (which runs through Westchester County) by replacing existing pipe and expanding compressor stations. 

This project would lock us into decades of fossil fuel dependence ‚Äî just when we need to be transitioning to clean energy. It‚Äôs risky, unnecessary, and completely out of step with New York‚Äôs climate goals. **Croton has the chance to be a climate leader by passing a resolution opposing this reckless project.**

Meet us outside Croton-on-Hudson Village Hall, where we‚Äôll rally together, then head into the board meeting to make powerful public comments demanding the Village take a stand.

Let‚Äôs pack the room and show our elected officials that Croton stands for climate justice, not fossil fuel expansion. Bring your friends, your voice, and your passion ‚Äî we‚Äôll have talking points and signs ready to go!

title: We Are The Bridge: Rise For Racial Justice Rally
description:
Remember George Floyd.

Remember the life that was stolen because of systemic racism and state sanctioned violence.

Remember how we responded, transforming our outrage and grief into an uprising that rocked the entire nation.

Remember that we‚Äôre not done. Our journey has only just begun.

To amplify the movement for Black lives, Brown Hope has convened a grassroots movement called We Are The Bridge: Rise for Racial Justice, a week of action between May 15 ‚Äî May 24 in recognition of George Floyd‚Äôs murder five years ago. This week of action features a series of community gatherings, culminating in a historic rally on May 24th at Revolution Hall and a peaceful march through downtown Portland and the Burnside Bridge.

We march for George Floyd. Breonna Taylor. Quanice Hayes. Kendra James. Eric Garner. Mike Brown. And so many others. We march because this injustice and suffering should never happen again. It should not take the deaths of more Black people for our elected and business leaders to do the right thing.

A grassroots coalition of Portland-based organizations have formed We Are The Bridge: Rise for Racial Justice‚Äî including Brown Hope, 50501 Portland, the Coalition of Black Men, the Oregon Working Families Party, Outside In, SURJ PDX, BIPOC Rise Moor Healing Center, Radical Rest, Veterans For Peace PDX Chapter 72, Restorative Roots Project, and Momentum Alliance. Together, we are calling for immediate action to expand opportunities for our local Black community to thrive‚Äî economically, socially, and spiritually.

Here‚Äôs the complete list of events organized for our week of action:

Nonviolence and De-escalation Training: 6pm on Thursday, May 15 at openHAUS (5020 NE MLK Blvd). Facilitated by the Portland Peace Team, this training teaches how to foster peace during moments of conflict using the CLARA de-escalation method.

Community Grief Circle:12:30pm on Saturday, May 17 at Alberta Park (1905 NE Killingsworth St). Experienced facilitators will lead activities that help attendees release emotional wounds connected to George Floyd‚Äôs murder and racial violence. Concludes with an optional community potluck.

Know Your Rights Training: 6pm on Thursday, May 22nd, Online. Facilitated by the National Lawyers Guild, the workshop covers constitutional rights related to activism and police interactions at first amendment events.

We Are The Bridge Rally and March: noon on Saturday, May 24th at Revolution Hall (1300 SE Stark St). A rally featuring Black and Indigenous leaders, followed by a peaceful march through downtown Portland with a moment of silence on Burnside Bridge.

As we remember George Floyd‚Äôs life and legacy, we must acknowledge that we have the responsibility to act. We Are The Bridge is encouraging supporters to help us build power by donating to local racial justice organizations and promoting the campaign on social media by using the hashtags #BlackLivesMatter and #BeTheBridge.

In 2020, Portland became a beacon of hope for the whole nation and the entire world thanks to 100 days of sustained action in solidarity with Black lives. This year, We Are The Bridge: Rise For Racial Justice is a collective antidote to the disease of moral bankruptcy currently plaguing our country. By participating in this week of action, we can make 2025 a defining year for Portland and our commitment to justice.

We are the heartbeat of this movement. Let‚Äôs work together to inspire a lasting movement of change.

For more information, visit: https://linktr.ee/BrownHope

#BlackLivesMatter #BeTheBridge
