This is outdoors but park has a large function inside the park so we are asked not to park inside. disabled people an either go with another driver and be let off in front of park or try to park way to the side of the entrance so as not to obstruct flow of incoming cars. Please display you disable notice on car window. Everyone else needs to park in the parking lot of Brown River Middle School next to Library on River Road a short walk to the park. Rest rooms in Library. Please see host Giovanna who will wear a green security vest.

We can hold a "Speak-Out" at the corner of VT-15 and River Road in the small triangular grassy area. You need to bring either a megaphone or microphone. It was too expensive for host to cover permit fee plus port-o-let and grassy area inside park. Consider wearing a mask as the last event there were pick-up trucks spewing dirty exhaust fumes at demonstrators.

Anyone who wants to help with security and a clean-up crew to make sure we leave areas we  occupy clean let host know.

title: Crawford Dems Memorial Day of Action
description:
Memorial Day weekend is a time to mourn, to honor and to celebrate
the lives and legacies of the brave men and women who fought and
died in order to maintain our freedoms.

Democracy and the Constitution are once again under attack...this
time by forces within our own nation. The rights of our veterans are
being ignored, their sacrifice dishonored, and programs supporting
and protecting them are being de-funded. But as we mourn the dead, we also need to fight for the living.

Freedom is not free. Stand up for veterans and freedom by joining us for a peaceful protest at the Veterans Memorial in Prairie du Chien.

Plan to speak out by displaying a sign to honor the memory of those
who have died, to support living veterans and their families, or other
signs supporting the freedoms that are at risk in our country.

title: North Omaha Visibility for John Ewing for Omaha Mayor and Democratic Candidates
description:
Join the Nebraska Democratic Party on Election Day - Tuesday, May 13th - for an exciting visibility event to remind people to vote for John Ewing for Omaha Mayor and for our Democratic City Council Candidates.

We will have signs for you or feel free to make your own. The main thing will be to encourage folks to vote for our candidates or to exercise their right to vote. 30th and Ames - next to Scooters.

title: This Is Our America ‚Äì Visibility Event for No Kings Day
description:
A military parade on the leader‚Äôs birthday, is not America. Citizens gathering peacefully, is.

Trump‚Äôs military parade could cost as much as $45 million. In our America, we organize and gather for free because we love our country. 

Join us on June 14, nationwide ‚ÄúNo Kings‚Äù Day of Action, for a peaceful, public demonstration of what we value as Americans: our country and all who call it home, and the rights and freedoms enshrined in the Constitution. 

Not a wanna-be dictator who uses Flag Day and the US Army‚Äôs 250th birthday as justification to throw himself a military parade at our expense.

title: NO KINGS Frisco, Texas

location.venue: FM 423 (both sides) between Main/King and Stonebrook

description:
June 14th is Flag Day and the 250th anniversary of the establishment of the United States Army. Coincidentally, it is also President Trump‚Äôs 79th birthday, and he is staging a $45 million military parade to appease his ever expanding ego! 

Who does that? Kings, tyrants, and dictators do.

In 1775, we began the fight for independence from the tyrant King George III of England. In 2025, we are reminding Trump and our elected representatives that America rejects his authoritarian actions, consolidation of power, disregard of law, and defiance of the courts. WE THE PEOPLE proclaim, once again: NO KINGS!  

We are joining millions of people all over the nation to rain on his taxpayer funded parade. We are reclaiming the flag and honoring those who have died protecting the democratic principles it represents. We are preserving our constitutional democracy. We are asserting the Army‚Äôs motto: THIS WE‚ÄôLL DEFEND! 

NO KINGS is a national day of action that welcomes people from all walks of life to join in peaceful, joyful, nonviolent dissent. We expect all participants to seek to de-escalate any potential confrontation with those who disagree with our values.

WHAT TO BRING:‚Ä®a friend, water, US flags, signs that reflect our theme - no kings, Army motto, democracy, rule of law, etc.

WHAT TO WEAR:‚Ä®sunscreen, light-colored clothing and hat, patriotic colors, stars & stripes, Army shirts, camoflage, Revolutionary War costumes, etc.

SPECIAL REQUEST:‚Ä®I‚Äôm looking for people that could bring the painting ‚ÄúThe Spirit of ‚Äô76‚Äù to life. For that, we need a piccolo player playing ‚ÄúYankee Doodle‚Äù and/or ‚ÄúThe Army Goes Rolling Along,‚Äù a snare drummer, and a flag bearer. I‚Äôm also looking for trumpeters to play ‚ÄúThe Star-Spangled Banner‚Äù and/or some bugle calls. Please contact me if you can help with this!

title: No Kings Peaceful Protest on Fairfield Ave. Bridge I-95 Overpass
description:
Join Good Trouble/Indivisible Norwalk for a peaceful protest on the Fairfield Ave. Bridge I-95 overpass in Norwalk, CT.

We'll wave signs to let people know there are NO KINGS IN AMERICA!

Our democracy was founded on the principle that no one is above the law ‚Äî not even a former president. We will not accept the regime's attempt to rewrite the rules, evade accountability, or crown anyone above the Constitution.

All participants must remain on public sidewalks and off the roadways. We will have safety marshals present to support nonviolent and community-centered action.

Let‚Äôs show the country and the world that we won‚Äôt be ruled ‚Äî we will rise!

Please email goodtroublenorwalk@gmail.com for parking/transit and accessibility information. All are welcome!

title: Hands Off! Rally

location.venue: Intersection of SE Mill Plain Blvd & Chkalov

description:
### The Rally to Protect Social Security is now the "Hands Off! Rally"! 

Join Indivisible Greater Vancouver and MoveOn-Clark County as we rally to tell the Trump/Musk administration to keep their "hands off" all of our vital services and communities!

Let's raise our voices - and our signs - to tell the Trump administration to keep their hands off our: 
- Social Security  

- Medicaid and Medicare  

 - Public Media: NPR, PBS  

 - Trans Community  

 - BIPOC Community  

 - National Parks 

 - Immigrants 

 - Autism/Disability Community 

- Veterans Services

 - Federal Workers -and more!

When we stand together in public to affirm our rights we let our community know that we stand with them. We'll gather at the southwest corner of Mill Plain and Chkalov in Vancouver, on the sidewalk by the Fred Meyer Shopping Center. Bring a sign that lets everyone know what you want the administration to keep their hands off!

PARKING NOTE: Fred Meyer and the businesses in the Trader Joe's/Shari's area have asked us not to park in their lots.

title: NO KINGS MASS PROTEST: MARCH for DEMOCRACY
description:
Join 50501 and Show Me Action for a NO KINGS MASS PROTEST and MARCH for DEMOCRACY on June 14 from 2 PM to 5 PM. We will rally at Kiener Plaza in Downtown St. Louis.

Schedule:
- 2 PM:  Rally featuring speakers

- 3 PM: March (Time subject to change) 
  
After the march, come back to Kiener Plaza for music and festivities.

Donald Trump thinks his rule is absolute, but in America, we don‚Äôt do ‚Äúkings.‚Äù Since the inauguration, the Trump administration and its enablers have operated as though they have a mandate‚Äîbut they don‚Äôt, and never did. They are going to extremes to empower Trump and enrich themselves, while cutting jobs and services for the rest of us. Now, they‚Äôre turning Flag Day into a celebration of Trump. 

We‚Äôre standing together against the abuses of power, cruelty, and corruption. On June 14, we gather to remind Trump and his enablers: America has No King!

Join millions nationwide on June 14 to march against authoritarian politics and billionaire takeover. Be part of a national moment that changes the conversation‚Äîand turns the tide.

Register to receive details and updates in the days leading up to the event.

title: EVERY SATURDAY in OMAK, WA 12-2PM
description:
BE EFFECTIVE: 
  EVERY SATURDAY let's SHOW UP at the light in Omak at 601 Omache Drive!¬†Any amount of time you can be there 12-2PM can be EFFECTIVE in¬†getting the eyes of our working community on us as they run errands in town, get groceries, and stop for gas on the way home.

BE CONSISTENT: 
  Let's mark our calendars for EVERY SATURDAY 12-2PM !!

BE LEGAL: 
  Please stay on public sidewalks. Do not block traffic.¬†Cross the street using the crosswalks when the traffic light allows.

BE SAFE: 
  Here is some de-escalation training:¬†
    https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_Pgmn9QRr48

BE INFORMED: Know your rights:
  https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=H4IBe-iAFtw

We are standing shoulder to shoulder with thousands across the country‚Äîthese events are part of something bigger. Events in all 50 states is proof of our commitment! 

We choose our families over their fortunes!! This is about organizing for our future! The rich are getting richer while the rest of us can‚Äôt catch a break.¬†This system was never built for us. But we‚Äôre building something better together!¬†They are afraid of our solidarity because it works!

SHOW UP in nonviolent protest in defense and support of working people in Okanogan County and everywhere.

title: Newburgh, NY: Rally to Tell Assemblymember Jacobson: Pass NY HEAT!
description:
Join Food & Water Watch and Citizen Action in Newburgh outside Assemblymember Jonathan Jacobson‚Äôs office for a rally to demand the Assembly pass the NY HEAT Act before the legislative session ends!

New Yorkers are being crushed by unaffordable utility bills, and the NY HEAT Act is the solution we need ‚Äî but Assembly Speaker Carl Heastie and legislative leadership are dragging their feet. 

This bill would put money back in the pockets of everyday people and tackle the climate crisis by:

1. Capping energy bills at 6% of household income ‚Äî saving 1.4 million overburdened households an average of $136/month‚Ä®
2. Ending the outdated "100-foot rule" that wastes $200 million/year expanding fracked gas pipes‚Ä®
3. Empowering clean energy upgrades instead of forcing costly fossil fuel hookups

The Senate has passed NY HEAT two years in a row. The Assembly must stop siding with fossil fuel interests and get it done this year!

Join us in Newburgh to pressure Assemblymember Jacobson to stand with us and fight for NY HEAT! We‚Äôll be rallying outside the office and then will go inside to deliver letters to staff.

title: Save Our Say - St. Francois County Democrats
description:
Rally for Respect MO Voters to help Save Our Say and protect the citizen initiative in Missouri.

As Missouri legislators return home after undermining voter-approved amendments, we will gather to demand that our voices be heard and respected. 

For over a century, Missourians have relied on the citizen initiative process to shape our state's laws. That process is now under attack. 

In April, Governor Kehoe signed SB22, also known as the "Let Politicians Lie Act.‚Äù This bill guts the initiative process, making it nearly impossible for everyday citizens to put measures on the ballot without political interference.

We are rallying to protect our democracy and support a proposed 2026 amendment that would: 
1-Ban politicians from overturning voter-approved amendments 
2-Protect the initiative process from added barriers 
3-Stop misleading ballot language that manipulates voters 

Together, we will send a clear message: We, the people, have the final say.

Event Highlights 
‚ú® Guest Speakers 
‚ú® Peaceful protest

title: Public Service Commission Candidate Open Forum
description:
As temperatures heat up and power bills rise, frustrated Georgians are starting to look at the Public Service Commission (PSC) for new regulations and to potentially bust up a Georgia Power monopoly.  Statewide PSC primaries for seats in Districts 2 and 3 will be held on June 17 and the general election will be on November 4.

Coastal Georgia for Democracy, the Savannah Indivisible group for Georgia District 1, will host a live open forum for voters to ask the candidates questions about their positions in advance of the election. The event will be held at the Coastal Georgia Center, 305 Fahm Street, Savannah, on June 12 at 6:00pm.  The free event is open to the public.

All PSC candidates have been invited to appear and will answer voters‚Äô questions regarding anything under the purview of the Public Service Commission, which includes how much Georgia residents pay for their electricity, landline telephones, and natural gas.  They also oversee the 811 ‚ÄúCall before you dig‚Äù line and items related to line interruptions when they are improperly monitored by contractors and residents. 

Confirmed attendees for the candidate forum include Alicia Blackstone in District 2 and Daniel Blackman, Peter Hubbard, Robert Jones, and Keisha Sean Waites in District 3.
 
The Georgia Public Service Commission has exclusive power to decide what are fair and reasonable rates for services under its jurisdiction. They must balance Georgia citizens' need for reliable services and reasonable rates with the need for utilities to earn a reasonable return on investment while not guaranteeing it. The Commission protects consumers' interests while abiding by legal standards in setting rates. All matters scheduled for public hearing are heard by the Commissioners or in special cases, by an appointed hearing officer in open session.

title: Pack City Hall for Safe Healthy Homes Act Hearing!
description:
Pack City Hall on Tuesday June 3rd for the Housing Committee hearing where they will VOTE YES on the Safe Healthy Homes bills!

When: Tuesday June 3rd 12pm

Where: City Hall 4th Floor!

What: City Council Housing Committee hearing on June 3rd to vote on the Safe Healthy Homes Act, 3 bills that strengthen renters rights by giving the City the power to proactively inspect rental units, hold bad landlords accountable when they violate the code, and ensure protections for renters against retaliation.

Why: We have a housing safety crisis in our city.  Hundreds of renters are going without heat in winter or living with mold, leaks, infestations, fire hazards, or other dangerous conditions that are affecting our health and even taking lives. We need City Council to PROTECT renters! We need YOU and every person who can make it to show up to make sure Council passes these bills,

JOIN US to show City Council that you want them to VOTE YES to protect renters! 


**EMAIL YOUR COUNCILMEMBER NOW: bit.ly/safehealthyhomes

title: SAVE OUR SAY: St. Louis Sit-In | Hands Around The Arch
description:
Respect MO Voters and 50501 STL invite you to our SAVE OUR SAY Sit-In at the Gateway Arch. As Missouri legislators return home after undermining voter-approved amendments, we will gather to demand that our voices be heard and respected.

For over a century, Missourians have relied on the citizen initiative process to shape our state's laws. That process is now under attack.
In April, Governor Kehoe signed SB22, also known as the "Let Politicians Lie Act.‚Äù This bill guts the initiative process, making it nearly impossible for everyday citizens to put measures on the ballot without political interference.

We are rallying to protect our democracy and support a proposed 2026 amendment that would:
1-Ban politicians from overturning voter-approved amendments
2-Protect the initiative process from added barriers
3-Stop misleading ballot language that manipulates voters

Together, we will send a clear message: We, the people, have the final say.

Event Highlights

 ‚ú® Guest Speakers

 ‚ú® Petitions, voter registration, calls & letters

 ‚ú® ‚ÄúHands Around the Arch‚Äù ‚Äì Circle of Unity

 ‚ú® Family-friendly and peaceful

 Bring: Signs, voice, water, snacks, chair/blanket, and comfortable shoes.

 Meet: In the grassy field under the Arch, river-facing side.

 Parking: Nearby garages and street parking available.

 Note: Please do not block or congregate on sidewalks.

title: Hailey Hands Off
description:
HAILEY HANDS OFF RALLY ‚Äî NOT LEFT, NOT RIGHT: FORWARD TOGETHER ‚Äî ALL ARE WELCOME. 

Hop Porter Park in Hailey. Saturday, May 17 beginning at 11:30AM

Join us as we kick things off with live music and uplifting words to inspire and energize. Then, we‚Äôll take to Main Street together in a powerful show of unity and purpose. Bring a lawn chair, your most creative homemade protest sign, and your voice. Everyone is welcome‚Äîcome stand in solidarity and make your presence count.

Rally for Due Process, Civil Rights & Liberties, US Constitution, Human Rights, Veterans Services, Children's Futures, Immigrants Lives & Families, Medicare, Medicaid, Medical Research, Reproductive Rights, Public Lands, Forest Service, BLM, National Parks, Environment.

Please wear comfortable shoes, bring a creative sign and a lawn chair.

title: Get Groovy Peaceful Rally & Hangout
description:

If you have a song request, please let us know!

title: Fight For Our Schools

address_lines: Placerville Drive and Ray Lawyer Overpass

description: This a local Indivisible event! We will be gathering at the Placerville Drive overpass, as well as Ray Lawyer overpass. There is also plenty of visibility on the walking trail by the freeway. This day is aligned with California Fight For Our School events, but bring flags and banners from whatever topic means most to you. We must remain vigilant. And save our democracy!

title: Hands Off Our Local Services
description:
This a local Indivisible event! On Friday, May 16 Indivisible Cortland County will hold a "Hands Off Our Local Services" Rally from 4:30-5:30 in front of Courthouse Park in downtown Cortland. This event is in protest of the "skinny budget" the administration recently unveiled. If enacted, this budget blueprint - which asks Congress to slash non-defense programs by more than $163 billion - will have a devastating impact on local services, including CAPCO and other programs.

As always, we will protest peacefully that day with our chants and songs, our signs and most important, our indomitable spirit!

See you there!

title: Rally at the Scituate Rotary
description: We are hosting a peaceful, community-based rally at the Scituate Rotary on 3A from noon-1:30PM on May 17th. Our theme is "Protect our Constitution". This is a well-trafficked intersection with lots of green space to stand with signs. Ample parking just off the Rotary at 7 New Driftway.

title: Alliance San Diego: Fight for Schools

tags.name: San Diego, Hands Off Our Healthcare, We Are Ca

description:
Alliance San Diego and We Are CA are joining  the San Diego Education Association & the California Teachers Association in San Diego for a statewide action to stand up for students and defend public education!

Dismantling the Department of Education, laying off thousands of dedicated department of education staff, appointing someone who has never spent a day teaching in a classroom to be our Secretary of Education‚Ä¶these are more than just headlines. They are direct threats to public education and the future of students and families across our community.

The Trump Administration is betraying public-school students and educators. Education is a non-partisan issue. Students in poverty and students with special needs deserve resources and support in our schools ‚Äì we can all agree on that. The Trump Administration is targeting students and families in our communities with these vicious plans to dismantle public education. It‚Äôs unacceptable and we‚Äôre fighting back. 

Details:

Start: Saturday, May 17, 2025 at 11:00 AM

Starting Location: Roosevelt Middle School, 3366 Park Boulevard, San Diego CA 92103

The event will include a march and a short program of local educators and community leaders who are parents in area public schools.

More Parking and Public Transit info: Free parking is available throughout Balboa Park, with detailed information available on the park‚Äôs website, and street parking throughout the North Park neighborhood. Participants wishing to use public transit should plan specific routes in advance using the MTS Trip Planner.

title: SAVE OUR SAY - St. Joseph/NW Missouri
description:
Rally for Respect MO Voters to help Save Our Say and protect the citizen initiative in Missouri.
As Missouri legislators return home after undermining voter-approved amendments, we will gather to demand that our voices be heard and respected.
For over a century, Missourians have relied on the citizen initiative process to shape our state's laws. That process is now under attack. In April, Governor Kehoe signed SB22, also known as the "Let Politicians Lie Act.‚Äù This bill guts the initiative process, making it nearly impossible for everyday citizens to put measures on the ballot without political interference.
We are rallying to protect our democracy and support a proposed 2026 amendment that would: 
1-Ban politicians from overturning voter-approved amendments 
2-Protect the initiative process from added barriers 
3-Stop misleading ballot language that manipulates voters
Together, we will send a clear message: We, the people, have the final say.

Event Highlights
 ‚ú® Guest Speakers
‚ú® Family-friendly and peaceful

title: Save Our Say Sit In
description:
Respect MO Voters and 50501 Missouri invite you to our SAVE OUR SAY Sit-In at Park Central Square. As Missouri legislators return home after undermining voter-approved amendments, we will gather to demand that our voices be heard and respected.
For over a century, Missourians have relied on the citizen initiative process to shape our state's laws. That process is now under attack. In April, Governor Kehoe signed SB22, also known as the "Let Politicians Lie Act.‚Äù This bill guts the initiative process, making it nearly impossible for everyday citizens to put measures on the ballot without political interference.
We are rallying to protect our democracy and support a proposed 2026 amendment that would: 1-Ban politicians from overturning voter-approved amendments 2-Protect the initiative process from added barriers 3-Stop misleading ballot language that manipulates voters
Together, we will send a clear message: We, the people, have the final say.

Event Highlights
 ‚ú® Guest Speakers
‚ú® Petitions, voter registration, calls & letters
‚ú® ‚ÄúHands Around the Square‚Äù‚Äì Circle of Unity
‚ú® Family-friendly and peaceful

Meet: In Park Central Square 
Parking: Nearby free parking garages and lots available.

New Yorkers are being crushed by unaffordable utility bills, and the NY HEAT Act is the solution we need ‚Äî but Assembly Speaker Carl Heastie and legislative leadership are dragging their feet to put it to a vote.

This a local Indivisible event!

While some in DC are hosting a massive, wildly expensive, taxpayer-funded display of US military might in DC to humor the ego of an aspiring authoritarian, here in the Waterville, Maine, area Indivisible Mid Maine will host a non-violent march and rally to celebrate and communicate the values and joys of the compassionate, sustainable, just community, country, and world we are striving to build. Join us!

This non-violent community event will consist of a march AND a rally. Participants are welcome to join us for any portion of the event. If you want to and are able to march, join us at 10 am at the town office in Fairfield, Maine, (19 Lawrence Ave.) with upbeat signs you can carry. At the Fairfield Town Office we will hear a very brief statement, reminding us all of the civil and human rights and values that are enshrined in both the Maine and US Constitutions and which we urge our leaders to uphold.

Marchers will then head down Lawrence Ave. to Main St., turn right and march along Main Street till it becomes College Ave. and then march along College Ave. until it becomes Main St., in Waterville, all the way to Waterville City Hall (1 Common St.). There the same brief statement that was delivered at the Fairfield Town Office will be repeated. We expect to arrive at City Hall around 11:30.

The distance of the march is about 3.4 miles, flat and with sidewalks all or most of the way. Participants should feel free to participate in any portion of the march, or the whole thing. Folks who want to travel the route by car or other vehicle are welcome to do so while we are marching, and may want to decorate their vehicles with signs similar to those that the marchers will be carrying.

After the march, participants will gather at a nearby location (TBD!) where the associated rally will begin at 11:30 and run until about 1pm, with music, light snacks, opportunities to meet and talk with others who share our non-violent, pro-democracy, pro-justice and human rights values, and to make and display relevant signs, etc.

Our goal is to continue building community here where we live, even as we engage in resistance against the larger forces that seek to destroy everything we hold dear. Please join us for all or part of this fun and uplifting event. If you can help with any of the pieces of the event, please reach out. And please watch this space for updates!

title: May 15 NATIONAL MOBILIZATION : Defend Birthright Citizenship at the U.S. Supreme Court

location.venue: Supreme Court of the United States

description:
# NATIONAL MOBILIZATION MAY 15 to the Supreme Court to Defend Birthright Citizenship!

## Rally Thursday, May 15 (day of oral argument)
## 9:00 a.m., before the 10 a.m. hearing.

On April 29, 2025, the civil rights organization BAMN submitted an amicus brief to the U.S. Supreme Court in the birthright citizenship cases Trump v. CASA, to speak on behalf of the National Resistance to Trump. It makes an argument no party and no other amicus curiae is presenting: that the Supreme Court must uphold birthright citizenship nationwide and not support Donald Trump‚Äôs ‚Äúplan to make America a fascist nation.‚Äù It defends the original intent of the Fourteenth Amendment that was won out of the Civil War: to extend birthright citizenship, a founding principle of the country, to all people regardless of race, to prevent the restoration of a racist caste system in America. 

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Below is BAMN‚Äôs amicus brief. Download as PDF: [Click Here!](https://drive.google.com/file/d/1L8oCzx-brMz3PUYkR_b32cPzZaPgsWMS/view)

## BRIEF AMICUS CURIAE OF B.A.M.N. (THE COALITION TO DEFEND AFFIRMATIVE ACTION, INTEGRATION AND IMMIGRANT RIGHTS AND FIGHT FOR EQUALITY BY ANY MEANS NECESSARY) IN SUPPORT OF RESPONDENTS

### Identity and Interest of the Amicus Curiae
The Coalition to Defend Affirmative Action, Integration and Immigrant Rights and Fight for Equality By Any Means Necessary (BAMN) is an integrated, youth-led civil rights and immigrant rights organization committed to building the new civil rights movement.

BAMN has a strong interest in the case because the above-titled case will affect the rights of citizenship for all people including all immigrants.

### Summary of Argument
The application for stay should be denied to prevent the American Catastrophe: Fascism from being enacted in the United States.

### Argument
No case before the Supreme Court, now or in the foreseeable future, is more important than this case. This case will settle the question of whether the majority of the Court will continue to act as the enabler of President Donald Trump‚Äôs plan to make America a fascist nation. If the pro-Trump majority concludes that Donald Trump has the right to amend the Constitution through an executive order, that ridiculous claim will sanction Trump‚Äôs belief that he, not the Constitution, is the arbiter of law in this country. If the pro-Trump majority decides that only the states and individuals who challenged his obviously unconstitutional executive order will have the right to a stay while the underlying substantive issues are being adjudicated, then this Court, like the Taney Court that decided Dred Scott v. Sanford, 60 U.S. 393 (1857), will bring this nation closer to another Civil War.

This Court‚Äôs majority has been neither fair nor objective in its ruling on multiple plainly unconstitutional decisions, Trump executive orders, or on the power of the Department of Government Efficiency (DOGE). It is obvious that Trump is getting away with the transformation of the U.S. into a fascist dictatorship, complete with deportations of people who have the clear right to be in the United States, in complete disregard of due-process rights and the ethnic cleansing of millions of people who live in the United States. The people that Trump is already holding in U.S., El Salvadoran and other modern-day concentration camps, make enormous sacrifices to keep cheap food on our tables, to bathe, feed, and provide other excellent care for the elderly and to do the dangerous and filthy jobs that other U.S. workers will not do. Trump has thumbed his nose at the Supreme Court‚Äôs order that he facilitate the return of Kilmar Abrego Garcia. It is time for this Court to defend the Constitution and stop the American Catastrophe of the fascist transformation of this country.

The question of whether the Fourteenth Amendment‚Äôs grant of birthright citizenship to everyone born in the United States includes children born to undocumented parents living in the United States was already a founding principle of this country under the Constitution of 1787. The principle of birthright citizenship was never an issue; it arrived in America with the Pilgrims. The only citizenship issue that appears in the Constitution is the question of naturalization, which gave Congress the ‚Äúpower‚Ä¶ to establish an uniform Rule of Naturalization‚Ä¶ throughout the United States.‚Äù Congress passed the Naturalization Act of 1790 which stated that ‚Äúfree white person(s)‚Ä¶ of good character‚Äù and two years of presence in the United States could become naturalized citizens of this country. Meanwhile, the practice of awarding citizenship to the children of arriving immigrants who could not themselves qualify to become naturalized citizens was always the law of the land.

The reason why the Constitution did not establish a single policy to determine who was a citizen was because that would have required resolving the question of whether the slaves and their children would be counted as citizens.

As a result, the states, not the Federal government, had the right to determine who could become a citizen within the boundaries of their territories. So in certain states like Wisconsin, Native Americans could become citizens of the state, despite the general prohibition against Native Americans receiving citizenship rights. Native Americans, while members of foreign nations, could be granted citizenship by having provision made for their citizenship in the treaties they signed with the United States government. The children of Native Americans who became citizens of the United States had the right to citizenship at birth.

The children of free black Americans had birthright citizenship in some northern states, where they were recognized as citizens. Challenging that right was impossible until the Dred Scott decision, which was supposed to ‚Äúsettle‚Äù the wars already breaking out between the abolitionists and the tyrants of slavery in Kansas and elsewhere, but only served to ignite the Civil War.

The Dred Scott decision was overturned when the mass power of the liberated black slaves and black Union battalions working in tandem with the hundreds of thousands of white young white soldiers smashed the power of the southern planters and finally opened the road for America to become the democratic, equal and free nation it had professed to be at its founding.

In the wake of the Civil War, millions of Americans had been radicalized by the second American Revolution and were determined to make sure that the war that had cost the lives of hundreds of thousands of Americans would make the plain words of liberty and rights for all persons real. The great Abolitionist Frederick Douglass describes, in his 1866 speech ‚ÄúReconstruction,‚Äù crowds of people demanding that their representatives in Congress stop catering to the pro-Southern President and the former slaveowners and take action, action which resulted directly in the passage of the Reconstruction Amendments:

"The members [of Congress] go to Washington fresh from the inspiring presence of the people. In every considerable public meeting, and in almost every conceivable way, whether at court-house, school-house, or cross-roads, in doors and out, the subject has been discussed, and the people have emphatically pronounced in favor of a radical policy. Listening to the doctrines of expediency and compromise with pity, impatience, and disgust, they have everywhere broken into demonstrations of the wildest enthusiasm when a brave word has been spoken in favor of equal rights and impartial suffrage. Radicalism, so far from being odious, is now the popular passport to power. The men most bitterly charged with it go to Congress with the largest majorities, while the timid and doubtful are sent by lean majorities, or else left at home."

The words of the Fourteenth Amendment were understood by Americans to mean what the words plainly say that all the children born in this country including those of Chinese and Japanese descent were entitled to birthright citizenship.

Under the leadership of Frederick Douglass and the Abolitionist movement in the streets arguing for the ratification of the Fourteenth and Fifteenth Amendments and the Abolitionists elected to Congress, the Constitution was transformed into a beacon of hope for the oppressed throughout the world. The southern slave-owning aristocracy that had kept the United States a land of hypocrisy and lies, steeped in depravity and the blood of countless black people was finally smashed forever.

### Conclusion
For the above reasons, the application should be denied.

title: Rally on Main Street
description:
This a local Indivisible event!  Bring your signs, pick your issue.  We will be on Main Street.  

We're organizing for a world where every family has housing, healthcare, fair wages, union protection, and safety‚Äîregardless of race, zip code, or immigration status. Retired people get the benefits that they have paid for all of their working life.  

They‚Äôre defunding our schools, privatizing public services, attacking unions, and targeting immigrant families with fear and violence. This is a war on working people‚Äîand we will not stand down. Using the principles of nonviolence and peaceful protest, we will stand together and stand strong.

This is the beginning of a new era‚Äîone where working families lead, immigrants are protected, and no one is left behind. This is not charity. This is not a request. We are reclaiming our power from corporate elites, and we will not be intimidated by Trump, Musk, or their billionaire backers. They‚Äôve ruled for too long. Their time is up.

STOP THE BILLIONAIRE TAKEOVER. WE ARE THE MANY. THEY ARE THE FEW. 

This is a peaceful rally.  Respect businesses and others using the sidewalks.

title: Poconos Together!  Rally in Stroudsburg
description:
** * Please sign up to receive updates before the rally, and to give us an estimate of attendance * **

Young or old, short or tall, fleet of foot or sturdy plodders ‚Äì friends and neighbors from all over the Poconos will gather in Stroudsburg to stand together in solidarity, and rally to protest the Trump administration's cruel and senseless attacks on our community:

- Our veterans and their healthcare

- Our Medicare

- Our teachers

- Our colleges, universities and students

- Our LGBTQIA+ siblings

- Our unions

- Our libraries

- Our immigrant friends and neighbors

- Our healthcare workers

- Our food, water and air safety

- Our national parks and public lands

- Our Social Security

- Our reproductive rights

- Our democracy

We will gather at 12:00 noon at Courthouse Square for check-in, and then stand on the sidewalk east of the square, on Monroe St. towards 6th Street for rally instructions before marching out (we'll have a different route this time).  We will stay on sidewalks, well away from the street, and keep safety first in mind.

Before going further:  Go ahead and sign up for our local [* No Kings *  National Day of Mobilization](https://www.mobilize.us/nokings/event/785149) rally on June 14

**Poconos Together!**  This means bring a few friends, some signs, and maybe something to share ‚Äì Mutual Aid of the Poconos is gathering items to distribute to those in need and unable to access other resources ‚Äì see the list of suggested items below.

**Poconos Together!**  This also means we DO NOT engage in confrontation with others who seek to disrupt our rally.  DO NOT give them the attention they want.  For the good of the movement ‚Äì disengage and de-escalate.  Ours is a peaceful rally, with nonviolence as a core principle.

**Poconos Together!**  Means we also support and bring business to local establishments, especially along Main Street in the areas where we will be standing.

** Please sign up to receive updates before the rally, and to give us an estimate of attendance **

Some suggested items to bring and donate if you can --

- Sunscreen, lotion, chapstick, deodorant

- Socks, combs, hair brushes

- Rain ponchos / slickers, ziplock bags

- Non-perishable food, water

- Small-amount gift cards to fast food places

- General toiletries (hygiene and first aid)

- - - - - - - - 

**We are stronger together!**  Let's continue building a movement to defeat our country's descent into authoritarianism.

[IndivisiblePoconos.org](https://IndivisiblePoconos.org)

[List of our meetings, rallies and other events](https://www.mobilize.us/indivisiblepoconos/?show_all_events=true)

title: UNITE FOR VETERANS, UNITE FOR AMERICA RALLY
description:
It's time to raise our voices and make our presence known to bring attention to the future of our beloved Veterans, their rights, their jobs and their future. We will be holding a rally/protest at the DELRAY BEACH VA CLINIC on Friday June 6th from 10AM - 12PM. We want to thank the employees who are still providing life saving services at the VA and protest the disgraceful cuts that continue to be made to the Veterans Administration. Our action is being done in cooperation with the National UNITE FOR VETERANS RALLY in Washington, DC.
Veterans are planning a massive rally in Washington, D.C., and elsewhere June 6 to protest cuts at the Department of Veterans Affairs and call for the protection of veterans' benefits and jobs, which are being hurt by the Trump administration's efforts to reduce the size of the federal government. The Unite for Veterans, Unite for America rally, is scheduled for the 81st anniversary of D-Day and is a call to preserve veterans' jobs and benefits and promote the protection of democratic principles.

title: 12 Days to Democracy! 12-Day 120-Mile March - Philly to DC - June 16-28
description:
This is it. This is the action.

Democracy has always been about the power of the people. It‚Äôs we, the people, who will fight the fight for a more just and equitable society.

This is the work‚Äì not of kings‚Äì but by all of us and for all of us. We‚Äôre the ones who have to travel the distance. 

And this is why, at this critical juncture in our history - when the laws and institutions protecting our right to fight are under attack like never before -  we have decided to take a very long walk.

Our walk ‚Äì a 120-mile journey from Philly to DC - will take us through towns, into cities, and along the trails of the East Coast Greenway, and we hope that it will look like the world we want to see: friendly and civil. Open to the joys of human variation, the friendliness of flexible minds, and also street dancing. This is a big, long mission; a walk/march, inspired by the big, hopeful, goodness-based, law-governed dream that is American democracy. We hope you‚Äôll consider joining us - for a mile, a city limit, the whole journey. 

BRASS TACKS: We are still hammering out the route, and you can see where we are below.  Days 1,2,3 are solid, and the rest are nearly solid (5/9).  We are seeking to obtain discounted hotel rates as well as tent options. The plan for hotels is to book a set block for the whole route which we will offer in one sum, and to have group discount codes for these hotels for people booking a subset of the nights.  Please reach out if you have more questions. This event will put you on our mailing list to be updated as soon as this information becomes available. 

FOR MORE DETAILS VISIT OUR WEBSITE: https://www.democracy12.com/

TO LEARN MORE, TO MEET THE ORGANIZERS OR TO LEARN HOW YOU CAN HELP THE EFFORT, ATTEND A ZOOM MEETING: https://mobilize.us/s/hXiRHp

THE ROUTE: 

Day 1: Mon, Jun 16. We start at noon at the Liberty Bell and head to Upper Darby, stopping at Murphy's Food Pantry and connecting with UDTJ

Day 2: Tue, Jun 17, To Chester¬†where MLK attended seminary school and cultivated his practice of non-violent protest

Day 3: Wed, Jun 18, To Wilmington¬†and the Harriet Tubman Garrent Riverfront Park

Day 4: Thu, Jun 19, Juneteenth, Through Delaware, passing through territory Tubman traversed on the Underground Railroad

Day 5: Fri, Jun 20, To Harford County

Day 6: Sat, Jun 21, To Baltimore County

Day 7: Sun, Jun 22, To Baltimore

Day 8, Mon, Jun 23, Rest day in Baltimore

Day 9: Tue, Jun 24, To Elkridge

Day 10: Wed, Jun 25, To Laurel

Day 11: Thu, Jun 26, To Greenbelt

Day 12: Fri, Jun 27, To Hyattsville

Final approach: Sat, Jun 28, To Washington, DC

title: Medicaid Monday!
description:
What: Protest with Flathead Democracy and 50501MT and Medical Device Drive for the Veterans Pantry!

When: Monday, May 19, 5-6 pm

Where: Intersection of hwy 2 and Nucleus in Columbia Falls (we will fill all sidewalks on all four corners!)

Why: Protect Medicaid!
Tell our Congressional Reps: Zinke, Daines, and Sheehy, NO cuts to Medicaid or we WILL take your seats from you!! Stop funding trillions in giveaways for Billionaires and Big Corporations with the People‚Äôs $$!

Bring a sign demanding Zinke, Daines, and Sheehy vote to protect federal funding for Medicaid. Montana has already voted to keep Medicaid expansions at the state level, but it doesn‚Äôt matter if the federal gov doesn‚Äôt fund the program! It‚Äôs time to make our voices heard! We are committed to peaceful protest and we ask everyone to stay on pedestrian walkways and follow traffic laws for the safety of yourself and others. Please bring a drink and snack and dress for unpredictable Montana spring weather! There will not be a march or rally with this event but we will be using our phones to send an email to our congressional reps.

We are also asking attendees to donate new or gently used medical devices for the Veterans Pantry Medical Supply closet (in Kalispell). They take most medical devices but their most popular requests are for: commode with bucket and lids, shower chairs, canes, transfer benches,  knee walkers, I-walk (pirate peg legs for knee to rest on while foot heals). Bring them to the event and we will take them to the Veterans Pantry!

Please feel free to park on the street nearby or at a business if you plan to patronize them as well. There is also a city park Marantette that has parking and in the surrounding neighborhoods.

Email Flatheaddemocracy@gmail.com if you‚Äôre interested in volunteering logistics or donating supplies.

There will also be a community sign making event on the evening of Saturday May 17. If you are on our email list we will email you details and if you‚Äôre not on our list, email flatheaddemocracy@gmail.com for instructions. Also email us if you‚Äôre interested in getting involved in the planning of the sign making event!

title: Sound the Alarm for Democracy

location.venue: Vigo County Annex Building of Terre Haute

description:
***If you are not from Terre Haute, Please start one of these near you! We would love this to be Nationwide!!!***

The Trump Administration and Elon Musk are acting with selfishness, hiding their actions in cowardice, and systematically dismantling the values upon which our country was built. The speed of the destruction has been truly horrific, and we the people are alarmed at the state of our democracy! So Indivisible Wabash Valley has launched the "Sound the Alarm for Democracy" weekly event. 

Every Monday at 12:05 pm, sound the panic on your car alarms, honk your horns, bang a drum, blow a trumpet, sing the Star Spangled Banner, or make noise however you can. The idea is that anyone can participate, no matter where they are, no matter what they are doing.

Those who are able will meet at the Vigo County Annex each week, everyone else, just make noise wherever you are: homes, schools, churches, jobs! We want to let our neighbors, our elected officials, and the rest of the world know that a lot of us are out here, still standing together to protect our democracy, and the rights to life, liberty, and the pursuit of happiness, fought for and defended for 250 years and counting.

JOIN US EVERY MONDAY!!
SOUND THE ALARM FOR DEMOCRACY

title: Kings & Clowns Rally

address_lines: South Oneida Avenue & East Kemp Street

description:
When a Clown moves into a Palace, he doesn‚Äôt become a King, the Palace becomes a Circus. While the clown throws himself a birthday party in Washington, the people in the Northwoods are defending our democracy!


WHAT IS ‚ÄúNO KINGS! NO CLOWNS!? It is a national day of action and mass mobilization in response to the increasing authoritarian excesses and corruption of the Trump administration. We‚Äôve watched as they‚Äôve cracked down on free speech, detained people for their political positions, threatened to deport American citizens, and defied the courts. They‚Äôve done this all while continuing to serve and enrich their billionaire allies. They think they rule‚Äîbut we are bigger than even their worst aspirations.
Donald Trump is planning a military parade in Washington, D.C. on June 14. This display of might is intended to intimidate opponents and solidify his image as a strongman on our dime‚Äîwe won‚Äôt stand by and watch!
Donald Trump thinks his rule is absolute, but in America, we don‚Äôt do ‚Äúkings.‚Äù Since the inauguration, the Trump administration and its enablers have operated as though they have a mandate‚Äîbut they don‚Äôt, and never did. They are going to extremes to empower Trump and enrich themselves, while cutting jobs and services for the rest of us. Now, they‚Äôre turning Flag Day into a celebration of Trump.
üí∞ He‚Äôs using OUR tax dollars to pay for HIS party: Donald Trump‚Äôs birthday celebration is expected to cost millions of our tax dollars, all while Republicans claim there‚Äôs no money for Social Security, SNAP, or Medicaid.
üëë We are united against kings: Trump has already indicated that he‚Äôs aiming for at least a third term, and now he‚Äôs planning a self-aggrandizing military parade in D.C But the American people don‚Äôt put up with kings. Together, we will mobilize in huge numbers to reject this corruption and abuse of power‚Äîit‚Äôs in our DNA as a country.
‚úã They‚Äôve gone too far: This is bigger than political disagreement. They‚Äôve defied our courts, deported American citizens, disappeared people off the streets, and slashed our services‚Äîall while orchestrating a massive giveaway to their billionaire allies. Enough is enough. For anyone who thinks he‚Äôs gone too far, this movement is for you.
We‚Äôre standing together against the abuses of power, cruelty, and corruption. On June 14, we gather to remind Trump and his enablers: America has No King!
Whether you're outraged by attacks on civil rights, skyrocketing costs, abductions and disappearances, the gutting of essential services, or the assault on free speech‚Äîthis moment is for you. Whether you've been in the fight for years or you're just fed up and ready to take action‚Äîthis moment is for you!
 He‚Äôs using OUR tax dollars to pay for HIS party.
Donald Trump‚Äôs birthday celebration is expected to cost millions of our tax dollars, all while Republicans claim there‚Äôs no money for Social Security, SNAP, or Medicaid.
We are united against kings.

They‚Äôve gone too far.
This is bigger than political disagreement. They‚Äôve defied our courts, deported American citizens, disappeared people off the streets, and slashed our services‚Äîall while orchestrating a massive giveaway to their billionaire allies. Enough is enough. For anyone who thinks he‚Äôs gone too far, this movement is for you.
The Army‚Äôs birthday isn‚Äôt about parades or pageantry ‚Äî it marks the beginning of America‚Äôs rejection of kings.
On June 14, 1775, the Continental Congress created the U.S. Army to stand up against a monarch who claimed absolute power. 250 years later, Donald Trump wants to twist that legacy into a personal celebration of himself.
That‚Äôs why we say: No Thrones. No Crowns. No Kings. No Clowns!
No Kings no clowns is about defending the ideals they fought for. This country doesn‚Äôt belong to strongmen. It  belongs to us!

Bring your signs and raise your voice for democracy and to protect our rights!  

This is a nonviolent event. Stay within your rights, don‚Äôt break laws, stay safe, stay peaceful, and avoid any risk you don‚Äôt feel comfortable with. Don‚Äôt obstruct traffic, impede pedestrians, or commit any acts of property damage. If counterprotestors appear, do your best to ignore them.  When people shout from cars, just remember that we are standing for their rights, too.  They just don't know it.

This is a busy intersection and cars drive fast.  Please stay on the sidewalk at least a few feet from cars.  We can spread out down the block and take a stand on the pedestrian overpass.  Safety is our top priority.  If you have any concerns during this event, please find a peace ambassador in an orange vest and they will help.

Then, we wave at the passing cars, looking friendly and putting a human face to the message. Thousands of drivers see our messages over time and many of them honk their approval. This planned event is more than just his birthday celebration; it is a direct challenge to our democratic values and our Constitution.  This administration has repeatedly defied court orders, unlawfully terminated federal employees, deported legal residents, and U.S. citizens without due process.  Moreover, he has obstructed women's rights, LGBTQ+ rights, and minority rights while undermining freedom of speech and freedom of the press.

We stand united in our refusal to accept this abuse of power.  Nationwide protests are being organized to support democracy and the rule of law.  Let us show our solidarity and make it clear, "No Kings in America, and this is not your flag, but America's Flag!" title: Honoring those who Sacrificed by Protecting Veteran Services
description:
This a local Indivisible event! Join us to honor those who gave the ultimate sacrifice and those who served and are serving in our military by demanding protections for the services they deserve.
Bring shelf stable items or personal care items (toothbrushes, shampoo etc) to donate.
Stand in solidarity with our Veterans and honor those who gave the ultimate sacrifice.

Bring: signs, flag cowbells, drums, and a loud voice for chants! Anyone can feel free to bring instruments, sing, start a chant, this is a movement by the people!

~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

Parking: Please carpool. Free parking: You can park at Staples, the overflow lots at the mall, or The Landing at Hyannis. Staples is only a minute or two walk away while the others are about a 15 minute walk from there. If you need to drop someone off before parking further away, please use the staples parking lot, not the side of a road. Paid parking: the airport, with the total cost $12 or less. (https://flyhya.com/parking-transportation/parking/) Public Transit: There is also the cape cod RTA. There are many lines that can connect you to Hyannis. From there, you get on the ‚ÄúBarnstable Villager‚Äù line and can get off at the mall or the landing at hyannis, or you can simply tap to get off when the bus approaches the rotary, they will stop if you tap the yellow line. (https://capecodrta.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Villager.pdf )

SAFETY: If it‚Äôs a smaller crowd, we can all park at Staples and stand on the grassy part near Nantucket Sound. If it‚Äôs a larger crowd, can spread out at four edges of the rotary (Wendy‚Äôs, church, bank, nantucket sound, NOT the airport side), so just stand near where you parked to avoid crossing roads unnecessarily. The rotary is a busy area and most parts do NOT have a crosswalk. If you park at the mall overflow, or The Landing at Hyannis, there is a crosswalk down there by the lights if you want to get to a specific grass area, the mall side will bring you to the church, bank or Nantucket sound, the landing at Hyannis side will bring you to Wendy‚Äôs or the airport. Remember, the drivers on the rotary are extremely distracted, so it's up to you to be mindful, cautious, and safe at all times.

Make sure to stay on the grass, a few feet away from the curb. Stay in the designated area. We are allowed to be on public/town land. We can walk the easements in front of the stores to reach the locations. Don‚Äôt go in the road and don‚Äôt go in the middle of the rotary. Police can shut us down if this happens. Attendees please help remind others to not go in or too near the road. Be mindful not to block cars visibility for entering the rotary. Notice where the ‚Äúexit‚Äù sign is for your area. The police will protect our right to protest, but if there are safety concerns, the police can and will shut us down. It is the responsibility of all attendees to follow all safety guidelines.

If there are counter protesters, DO NOT ENGAGE AT ALL. If attendees engage, the police can shut us down. We don‚Äôt want this to happen!! Notify a safety warden (in a neon vest) in your area of any disturbance immediately before it can escalate. Everyone must act responsibly and obey instructions from organizers and police. Attendees: Do not engage. Step away. Alert a safety warden. Help safety wardens remind others of these guidelines. Your calm response is your power.

If you feel you need to start videoing for any reason, you are encouraged to do so. It will be good record keeping. Please continue to ignore the agitator(s) and find a safety warden, in a neon vest. We don‚Äôt expect any violence. We expect this to be a peaceful, safe, event to show our care, community, and courage.

Before you leave: Make sure to leave the space better than when you arrived. If anything needs to be cleaned up (signs, trash etc.) please lend a hand. Also, if you‚Äôre not already part of an ‚ÄúIndivisible‚Äù group, make sure to get a ‚Äúpalm card‚Äù before you leave, with a QR card of how to join. There will be donation buckets if you would like to leave a few dollars to support the ‚ÄúIndivisible‚Äù groups on Cape Cod.

Sign up to receive emails whenever there's a new post on our website: https://capecodwomenforchange.com/subscribe-to-get-latest-posts/

description:

The DOT does not like things attached to the fence. They may visit, so be prepared to not have anything attached. Never drape anything over the fence, even with ropes, because it would be very dangerous if it accidentally fell onto the highway.

Other Logistics No Port-A-Potties are available but there is a McDonalds nearby if needed. Please take everything you brought away with you and leave the site totally clean.

Come join like-minded folks to demand that Trump, Musk, and the Republican-led Congress stop their unconstitutional power grab and the cruel destruction of our federal government.

We will hold banners, signs, and flags, and we'll wave to passing motorists. Many will beep and wave back at us, which feels nice! We'll show people that they're not alone and help give them the courage to join us and take a stand.

Please come out whether or not you have a sign or banner or flag. More people is better!

Come when you can and leave when you must. You needn't be present for the entire time.

We may see a counter protester. If so, please DO NOT ENGAGE.  Either ignore them or reply with "have a nice day". Let's spend our time and energy waving to motorists. Let's keep things 100% non-confrontational in words and body language. As always all of our events are peaceful and non-violent.

title: L.A. Trump Must Go Now! Protest - Rally and March
description:
Take to the streets on May 17 in mass protests to make Trump Must Go NOW! known in cities and towns. These protests combined with dramatic banner drops, vigils, and other creative nonviolent actions across the country in the days going into Saturday, on the day itself, and in the days after can make get this demand seen by millions:

We all feel it ‚Äì the atrocities are relentless. Another right snatched away. Someone else disappeared. Due process shredded. Law firms targeted. Universities threatened. Books banned. Immigrants shipped to overseas forever-prisons. Trump promises to disappear ‚Äúhome-growns‚Äù (US citizens) next. Trans people banned from the military. It feels impossible to keep up.

We cannot win by chasing each attack as it comes, overwhelmed and outmatched by the vicious speed of Trump's fascist regime. Nor can we wait until 2026 or 2028.

But there is a way to win ‚Äì a way to defeat this fascist juggernaut.

It is time to come together to take the offense against the whole damn thing ‚Äî infusing ‚ÄúTRUMP MUST GO NOW!‚Äù into all the resistance movements forging a mighty force to stop the regime from carrying out its horrific fascist assault on people here and around the world.

The Refuse Fascism Call to Conscience/Call to Act breaks down the strategy to oust this regime through mass, sustained, nonviolent protest and resistance. Read it. Sign it at RefuseFascism.org/act Spread it to others.

Then, On May 17, join with others across this country to make a big leap in projecting this demand ‚Äì Trump Must Go Now! ‚Äì to the tens of millions who are heartsick and furious about all Trump is doing. Let them see there is a movement for them to join with a real strategy to win. Keep raising this demand all summer long, including at the nationwide protests called for June 14,‚ÄúNo Kings Day‚Äù!

If we act with courage and heart, if we unite all who can be united from diverse political perspectives, we have the numbers and the power to reclaim the future.

In the Name of Humanity, We Refuse to Accept A Fascist America!

title: Mondays @ McCormick's
description:
This is an EMERGENCY! Senate Protest Event in Philadelphia Continues This Week and For the Foreseeable Future.

Now called "Monday's at McCormick's" each Monday at noon - rain or shine - Here's why:

We are living in a MAGA-republican Coup. We were warned. Now it's here!

Here at home our democratic rights are being eroded and the Trump/Musk team is putting us all in danger. The limits of Executive power against the courts are being tested every day. If Trump decides to ignore the courts, there is very little they can do to enforce their decisions and unless Congress acts, it would be a true constitutional crisis. (And so far, Congress is controlled by the MAGA movement and the Democrats have not done enough to stand up and fight back.) It could even spiral down into outright civil war as competing factions and states careen between untested solutions to protect their own interests and those of their constituents and funders. There is real harm being done across the entire domestic sector. Layoffs, program cuts for the needy and for the average US resident, persecution of law abiding immigrants and students and other activists for simply speaking their mind and organizing constitutionally protected protest. Fear is also their weapon.

Our international role is being flipped on its head - yes, the US has always had a questionable foreign policy, providing aid and promoting democracy and human rights - to a degree - on the one hand, while at the same time invading other countries for the good of corporate profits and geopolitical dominance. Trump considers a policy to outright invade counties like Mexico and Greenland in violation of international law and to extend US power - A clear expression of Empire! Trump is considering power grabs not unlike those that the Nazi regime in Germany perpetrated in search of "Lebensraum", (Living Space) a euphemism for territorial conquest. And they got away with it (for a while) because the people who stood up were either jailed, exiled or murdered. The rest were either regime supporters (Like the solid 30% base of the MAGA movement) or went along out of fear of retribution. We cannot let fear prevent us from standing up this time. History will judge us.

We now have a true oligarchy in the US and we must fight back!

The Trump administration‚Äôs illegal actions and relentless efforts to dismantle protections for vulnerable communities ‚Äî both here in the U.S. and abroad‚Äî have made clear we are in the midst of an authoritarian takeover not unlike what has happened in Orban‚Äôs Hungary. 

His plan to "Own Gaza" and move out Palestinians is NOT a plan to destroy Hamas and increase Israeli security - it is ETHNIC CLEANSING pure and simple. It's a land grab. All for development rights and to secure a seaport access to natural gas deposits off the shore of Gaza in the Mediterranean Sea. The Levant gas field includes the shores of historic Palestine (Israel and Gaza), Syria, Lebanon and, on the opposite side, the island of Cyprus. This field is estimated to contain about 122 trillion cubic feet of natural gas. So it will accelerate the climate emergency. 

As we all know Trump/Musk plan to get rid of a number of government agencies that protect our health, livelihood and constitutional rights. - the EPA is on the hit list. The Department of Education is too. So, is the CDC, the NIH and many other important agencies that protect the US public.

As we all know - thousands have already been fired, causing chaos and havoc and real harm to both dedicated civil servants AND people served by life affirming programs voted on by the U.S. people and enacted, in most cases, by the U.S. Congress. The Administration may have authority to make staffing decisions, but as is the case with the Department of Education - many of these agencies can only be eliminated by acts of Congress - Trump has overstepped his legal authority.

Thankfully, the courts have, so far, acted as a check on much of Trumps clear and blatant abuses of executive power. But we cannot count on the courts, particularly the US Supreme court, which has been stacked by Trump appointees and ideologues friendly to executive power. 

Resistance is NOT futile - it is essential. 

We are launching "Monday's at McCormick's" each Monday at noon - rain or shine - we will assemble peaceably - as is our constitutional right - outside Senator McCormick's Philadelphia office until Senator McCormick agrees to meet with us and support our demands: (These will change as conditions develop)

 1 - Stop voting for legislation inspired by Trump's project 2025 agenda - a plan to slash Medicaid, gut school lunch programs, and shut down nursing homes while handing more power to billionaires like Elon Musk. 

2- Roll back Trump's mean spirited and Unconstitutional funding pauses. Shutting down USAID is already killing people in need all over the World. Cuts to programs here in the US could do the same. Funding for these programs are up to the Congress and the US people to decide, not Trump! 

That's just for starters. Overall we want Senator McCormick to represent us all, not just his rich friends. We want Senator McCormick to DO HIS JOB!
The stakes could not be higher. The administration is pushing an authoritarian agenda that threatens our democracy, our rights, and the well-being of millions here at home and around the planet. 

We have the power to resist‚Äîand we must use every tool at our disposal to stop them.

title: People over Profit: Billionaires Shouldn‚Äôt Rule America
description:
## **People over Profit: Billionaires Shouldn‚Äôt Rule America**

The United States is not a corporation, and our government is not a for-profit enterprise. Elon Musk is not a government official. He‚Äôs a billionaire with no accountability to the American people, and nobody voted for him. Our democracy deserves better.

Musk and Trump will only be defeated by a massive, bipartisan movement of everyday Americans standing up against corruption, authoritarianism, and huge tax breaks for the rich, while fighting for the programs that working people need.

** This is a BIPARTISAN, PEACEFUL Protest** 
**No violence or Destruction of Property will be tolerated** 

**The People over Profit Movement**

Right now, millions of Americans across the political divide are struggling. 60% live paycheck to paycheck, many earn very low wages, and 85 million lack proper health insurance. College is too expensive for young people, a quarter of seniors live on $15,000 a year or less, and childhood poverty is among the highest in the world. We also face a severe shortage of affordable housing.

At the same time, the wealthiest Americans, like Elon Musk, Jeff Bezos, and Mark Zuckerberg, are getting richer. Since Trump‚Äôs election, their combined wealth has grown by over $200 billion‚Äîmore than the bottom half of the country. Meanwhile, the middle class shrinks, and democracy is at risk.

Our goal is to protect democracy and create an economy that works for everyone, not just the rich. As the wealthiest country in the world, we have the potential to use new technologies to improve everyone‚Äôs lives, but instead, most of the wealth goes to the people who need it the least.

We must make healthcare a human right, raise wages to a living standard, improve public education, address the housing crisis, create good-paying jobs to fight climate change, and end all forms of discrimination.

**We the People believe that in the richest country in the history of the world we must establish that:**

1. Healthcare is a human right and must be available to all regardless of income.

2. Every worker in America is entitled to earn a decent income. We must raise the minimum wage to a living wage and make it easier for workers to join unions.

3. We must have the best public educational system in the world, from childcare to vocational training, to graduate school ‚Äì available to all.

4. We must address the housing crisis and build the millions of units of low-income and affordable housing that we desperately need.

5. We must create millions of good paying jobs as we lead the world in combating the existential threat of climate change.

6. We must abolish all forms of bigotry.

title: Join the National Day of Action for Single Payer Healthcare!
description:
## It‚Äôs time to end the health care crisis. Join the National Day of Action for Single Payer! Saturday, May 31st 1pm-3pm.

Our health care system is broken‚Äîand it‚Äôs **killing** us. For-profit insurers and corporate middlemen deny care, drive up costs, and profit off our pain. Decades of piecemeal reforms have only made things worse: skyrocketing prices, massive waste, and some of the worst health outcomes among wealthy countries.

**We say: enough.**

### We demand a system that puts people before profit‚Äîwhere health care is treated as a human right, not a business.

#### We are calling for:

- The elimination of private insurance companies and for-profit care.

- A national, publicly funded single payer program that covers everyone‚Äîcomprehensively and equitably.

- A transformation of our health care system to serve communities, not corporations‚Äîfreeing caregivers from corporate control and putting power in the hands of the people.

This event is happening in Portland, but we‚Äôre not stopping here. Activists are organizing sister actions across Oregon‚Äîfrom the coast to the high desert. Stay tuned for more info on how to plug in near you!

On the **National Day of Action**, people across the country‚Äîpatients, nurses, union members, small business owners, neighbors and organizers‚Äîwill take to the streets to demand real change. This is about building a mass movement to take profit out of care and put National Single Payer on the political agenda‚Äînow.

Bring your families (kid friendly!), neighbors, friends, everyone you know and join us to turn collective outrage into collective action: put National Single Payer on the nation‚Äôs agenda!

title: Stop Elon Musk Rally!

### NEW SATURDAY TIMES 
Through the month of May our Saturday Stop Elon Musk! rallies will be from 4 pm - 6 pm. We've made this time change to allow people to attend more than one event on Saturdays. Thank you for your dedication to showing up for democracy!

We at IGV strongly believe that peaceful, non-violent activism offers social movements the most power to effect change. Through peaceful protests, we set an example of making our voices heard with dignity, empowered by truth. IGV does not condone intimidation, threats, vandalism, interference with access to a business, or any other lawless actions. If instigators or our opponents attempt to violate our commitment to non-violence, we will try to de-escalate them and will end the event if needed to maintain a safe environment.

title: Street Rally to Defend the Constitution - Kirkland
description:
Exercise your free speech - while you still have it.  Join Walt and Jerrie in their ongoing protest of the harmful administration's policies every Saturday until the FFOTUS is removed from office. 

** Kirkland along Central Way between 3rd and 6th Streets **

Kirkland Safe Rally Rules:

- Do not block vehicles, bikes or pedestrians.

- Do not stand in bicycle lanes or the medians.

- Do not block traffic entrances to businesses. 

- Do not use sound amplification.

- Do not troll the crosswalks and watch carefully for turning vehicles. Frequent use of crosswalks slows traffic an annoys the people we're trying to reach. 

We have had little resistance but:

- Do not engage with Trumpers ‚Äì Smile, wave & nod.

- If you feel threatened, yell out ‚ÄúMarilyn Monroe‚Äù and those closest will surround you. All others should use their cameras to record the action. If serious, call 911. 

Let's Have a Fun and Safe event and make our voices heard!

Read about and listen to Rachel Maddow on how sustained, local action is so important in shaping public sentiment. This matters. You matter. Thank you for joining us! https://www.thedailypoliticususa.com/p/rachel-maddow-explains-how-protests

title: Protest Elon Musk's Illegal Government Takeover #TeslaTakedown - Saturdays
description:
PLEASE READ COMPLETELY before attending!

This is a peaceful, nonviolent protest on the sidewalk in front of the Palo Alto Tesla showroom. 

Make sure not to block the Tesla driveway entrances. We will stay completely on the public sidewalk and off of Tesla property, and cross only with lights. 

Wear your favorite wig, big hat, or costume. We want to have fun and to feel like a party during our demonstrations! Signs, musical instruments, drums, flags, and similar items are welcome.

This is a peaceful demonstration, and any conflicts or altercations will not be tolerated. Walk away if one arises and report it to the demonstration leader on site if it is a serious altercation. We will comply with requests from the police, including if we are asked to leave. 

Do not boo or confront Tesla drivers or cars, or Tesla employees. Remember that most Tesla drivers are our allies, and many are protesting with us!

#BoycottTesla #DivestFromTesla
accessibility_notes: Takes place on the sidewalk outside the Tesla dealership

title: Stand Up, Superior! - A Tesla/Trump Takedown
description:
Come join us on Saturdays from 11am to 2pm to peacefully protest the corruption and hatred coming from the head of our government currently. 

This will be an on-going event until the madness stops, and unfortunately, it seems as though we might be doing this for a while.
Just to be clear, signing up does not mean you are required to be at every protest. 

The sole purpose of this website is to let you know that people will be there on McCaslin Blvd. every Saturday until we are heard and changes are made.

For your mental and physical health, I recommend taking the occasional Saturday off! Know that others are there keeping the event going strong.

There may be individuals who approach on foot and try to provoke us. 
It is my hope that you‚Äôll be able to ignore them and redirect your attention to the individuals standing beside you. 

It is a requirement of all attendees that you help uphold our commitment to non-violence and de-escalate any potential confrontation with those who disagree with our values. 

Here are some suggestions to keep this a peaceful, civil protest: 

‚Ä¢ Keep away from the Tesla employees, dealership, and their immediate surrounding property. Protest events at Tesla locations or other Musk properties should be focused on Elon Musk's role as a political actor and government agent. Protests should not be aimed at attacking the business interests of Tesla or their customers. 
‚Ä¢ Stay on the sidewalk next to the public streets and keep off the lawn next to their building. 
‚Ä¢ Stare past any agitators like they don‚Äôt exist. 
‚Ä¢ Start a conversation about something random with someone near you. 
‚Ä¢ Focus on music and the people driving by cheering in support. 

For your safety and the safety of those around you, consider not engaging with anyone that tries to provoke you. 

Parking and What to Bring:

‚Ä¢ There is plenty of parking at the mall and near the Starbucks across the street from the Tesla Dealership.
‚Ä¢ Bring a sign that expresses your feelings/what you're there for. 
‚Ä¢ Water to stay hydrated, a sweater/coat, sunscreen, a hat, masks if you feel it necessary.
‚Ä¢ Something to sit on if you want to attend, but cannot stand for hours on end.
‚Ä¢ A playlist with upbeat music and a bluetooth speaker to help keep people around you positive and motivated.

‚ÄúCourage is not the absence of fear, but rather the assessment that something else is more important than fear.‚Äù ‚Äì Franklin D. Roosevelt 

Resist. Dissent. Persist.

title: Tesla Takedown Rockville, MD
description:
This a local Indivisible event!

About this event
This a local Indivisible event! About this event Elon Musk's seizing control of the US Government needs to be stopped. We need to stand up and let the world know how we feel.

We're leading a nonviolent rally outside of the Rockville Tesla showroom to let the community know supporting Tesla is bad for democracy, and to remind our entire community that Elon's lawless actions are dangerous and won't be tolerated.

This is a peaceful action. We will not enter the business, nor stop people from entering or exiting the property. No violence or threats against anyone will be tolerated.

Bring your own signs encouraging people to honk for democracy and sharing your thoughts about Elon's wrecking of our government. Let's show the world that we won't tolerate his threat to government of the people, by the people, and for the people.

We will stay on the public sidewalks and not obstruct traffic.

See you there!
accessibility_notes:
We counted over 750 people on our Global Day of Action . Let's double that number in the weeks ahead. The friendly, festive atmosphere and cars honking in support has been great. This is a wonderful community of welcoming people who are banding together to save our democracy. Thank to you all for showing up every Sat. And welcome to newcomers!!

A core principle behind all Indivisible events is a commitment to nonviolent action. We expect all participants to seek to de-escalate any potential confrontation with those who disagree with our values.

title: Stop Elon Musk!
description:
Join Indivisible Greater Vancouver (IGV) and MoveOn Clark County for a peaceful protest at Vancouver's Tesla dealership!

Unelected billionaire Elon Musk is stealing our money, our data, and our democracy. He's making decisions about our government behind closed doors, just to funnel money into his own hands. Let's stand united to say 'No Oligarchs!'

We'll march on the sidewalk/right of way outside Vancouver's Tesla showroom on Fourth Plain Blvd., staying on public property. Park on the street or in the surrounding neighborhood - not in business parking lots. For those who don't want to hunt for a parking spot, you can take the Green Vine bus from the transit center at the Vancouver Mall. It runs every 15 minutes and it's $1.25 each way. This line stops at Andresen Rd along Fourth Plain. Bring a large sign to let everyone know we stand united against Musk, DOGE, and unelected oligarchs!

We at IGV strongly believe that peaceful, non-violent activism offers social movements the most power to effect change.Through peaceful protests, we set an example of making our voices heard with dignity, empowered by truth. IGV does not condone intimidation, threats, vandalism, interference with access to a business, or any other lawless actions. If instigators or our opponents attempt to violate our commitment to non-violence, we will try to de-escalate them and will call law enforcement if needed to shut down such unauthorized activity.

We know many of us have very strong feelings about issues and people at this time. If you feel that you may have difficulty remaining nonviolent, please do not attend this activity.
