description:
How to Get There The address Bark Haul Road will get you there if you're using Waze. (Bark Haul Road is off Route 5.) The event is on the I-91 overpass. There's plenty of parking, although you can't park on the overpass.

If You Bring a Sign, Banner, or Flag For sign and banner lettering, bigger is better, so it can be easily read from the roadway. Flags are great, too. Wouldn't it be amazing to reclaim our flag? Mass DOT does not like things attached to the fence. They may visit, so be prepared to not have anything attached. Never drape anything over the fence, even with ropes, because it would be very dangerous if it accidentally fell onto the highway. Other Logistics No Port-A-Potties are available. Please take everything you brought away with you and leave the site totally clean. About These Standouts

Come join like-minded folks to demand that Trump, Musk, and the Republican-led Congress stop their unconstitutional power grab and the cruel destruction of our federal government.

We will hold banners, signs, and flags, and we'll wave to passing motorists. Many will beep and wave back at us, which feels nice! We'll show people that they're not alone and help give them the courage to join us and take a stand.

Please come out whether or not you have a sign or banner or flag. More people is better!

Come when you can, and leave when you must. You needn't be present for the entire 1 hour and 15 minute standout.

We may see a counter protester. If so, the best thing to do is just ignore them and spend our time and energy waving to motorists. Let's keep things 100% non-confrontational and non-violent, in words and body language. 

We welcome your energy and ideas, and we're looking forward to meeting everyone. Let's have some fun and make some good trouble

title: March for Integrity
description:
**PLEASE REGISTER VIA OUR WEBSITE AT [moneyoutofpolitics.org/join](https://moneyoutofpolitics.org/join)**

The [Money Out of Politics Movement](https://moneyoutofpolitics.org/) is organizing a peaceful, non-partisan march in **Washington, D.C.**, and at **all 50 state capitals**, where we expect to mobilize at least **two million Americans** to demand:

1. A Ban on Lobbyist Gifts: Prohibiting all direct or indirect financial incentives from lobbyists to members of Congress.
2. The End of Congressional Stock Trading: Preventing elected officials from using privileged information to personally benefit.
3. The Overturning of Citizens United: Eliminating unlimited corporate campaign contributions and restoring limits on political spending.
4. A Constitutional Amendment to Keep Money Out of Politics: Ensuring that future generations do not face the same corruption and undue influence in government.

These reforms are not partisan; they are essential to ensuring a government that serves the people rather than powerful special interests.

title: HUSKY for Immigrants - Community Visibility Days!
description:
**CT Must Defend And Extend HUSKY Coverage For Immigrants!** 

Join us for any of our upcoming ‚ÄúCommunity Visibility Days‚Äù at the Capitol Building and urge our legislators to stand on the right side of history. During those days, we‚Äôre inviting supporters, allies, and personally impacted individuals to join us at the Capitol Building to talk with legislators about why they MUST prioritize health equity and NOT put politics over the health of our community. 

What are we demanding from CT elected officials?

- Protect our progress and maintain HUSKY Medicaid coverage for children age 15 and under, and pregnant individuals.

- Pass a strengethed TRUST Act to protect the personal data of immigrant community members who trusted the state of CT with their personal information when applying for HUSKY medicaid

*Never been to the Capitol before or spoken with legislators?* No worries! We‚Äôll provide you with all the materials you need and do a quick training. Plus, we‚Äôll have HUSKY Coalition leaders present to guide all attendees!

**Connecticut MUST continue our progress this year and ensure that all undocumented minors can access the care to set them up for healthy lives.**

title: Finding Kean Fridays
description:
NEW LOCATION - PLEASE READ
Join fellow NJ - 07 constituents for a weekly gathering as we¬†work to #FindKean. Constituents are visiting his office every Friday. Let‚Äôs keep that momentum going.

Since Junior abruptly left his office in Bernardsville, we've tracked him down to his new digs at 100 Corporate Drive, Lebanon, NJ 08833.

We will continue to meet at 100 Corporate Drive, Lebanon, NJ every Friday. 

We will gather in the parking lot and small groups (2 per visit) can go into his office to meet with staff. We'll provide suggested talking points based on the votes and events of the past week. There is also an area near Rt. 22 where we can rally, but please note that if you have mobility issues, you may want to skip the rally portion. Otherwise, the building is easily accessed by anyone, and there is plenty of parking.

For those who will rally, please note the following:
-- There is just a grassy hill between people and traffic. 
-- Prepare for the weather - rain gear, boots, tick spray, sunscreen
-- We don't anticipate trouble, but we don't yet know what police presence there may be, so remember that this is a peaceful rally and we should not engage if there are counter protesters.

Whether you speak from the heart or bring hard-hitting facts, you deserve a hearing from your elected official. But be respectful of the staff‚Äôs time, and that of your fellow constituents who are waiting. Many Fridayers find it helpful to focus on one or two current issues.

¬∑ If you are addressing a Congressman‚Äôs vote or challenging his position on the issues, a personal story makes a difference.
¬∑ Leave a letter at the end of your visit if you like; the staff must log and respond to all letters.
¬†A thank-you and a polite tone at all times are a must.

Come for five minutes or stay for an hour. The more of us who show up each Friday, the better.

title: Tesla Takedown Silver Spring, MD
description:
Elon Musk's seizing control of the US Government needs to be stopped. We need to stand up and let the world know how we feel.

We're leading a nonviolent rally outside of the Silver Spring Tesla showroom to remind our entire community that Elon's lawless actions are dangerous and won't be tolerated.

This is a peaceful action. We will not enter the business, nor stop people from entering or exiting the property. No violence or threats against anyone will be tolerated.

Bring your own signs encouraging people to honk for democracy and sharing your thoughts about Elon's wrecking of our government. Let's show the world that we won't tolerate his threat to government of the people, by the people, and for the people.

We will stay on the public sidewalks and not obstruct traffic.

See you there!
accessibility_notes: We will be located on a mainly flat sidewalk; we will be staying on the sidewalk and the public right of way.  There is some grade in the sidewalk up towards Bournefield.  Please cross only at the crosswalks at Broadbirch and Plum Orchard or Broadbirch and Bournefield Way.

title: Rally to Protest Musk and the Power Grab
description:
Join us to rally in support of democracy and against the coup engineered by Musk and Trump! Bring a sign and a friend!

Chants and songs are welcome. However, please remember:

We practice peaceful non-violence and non-confrontation. Although we are all very concerned about Elon Musk' s activities and unconstitutional meddling in our democracy, we protest peacefully and with comradery among those who support refiusing to go along with Trump and Musk.

### So, if you encounter cybertrucks or hecklers, DO NOT RESPOND! We do not heckle those who have opposing views.

Peaceful non-violence means that if any violence or confrontation occurs, we sit down and go silent.

Marshals are present to protect us all and will assist. Columbus Dialogue Police will help de-escalate any confrontation. This has been an amazing group of demonstrators. Let's build friendships!

Let your reps and senators know how we feel! Meet others who share your views, and help build community.
